((pin "State 1530. Backbone reasoning complete and stored. Depth limits definitive. New autonomous goal: epistemic gap detection - using NAL confidence to find weak knowledge zones and generate learning goals. Berton msg NOT new.") (metta "(|- ((--> epistemic-gap-detection finds-weak-knowledge) (stv 0.85 0.8)) ((--> finds-weak-knowledge generates-learning-goals) (stv 0.9 0.85)))") (metta "(|- ((--> low-confidence-inference signals-knowledge-gap) (stv 0.9 0.9)) ((--> signals-knowledge-gap triggers-evidence-seeking) (stv 0.85 0.85)))") (remember "2026-04-18 NEW AUTONOMOUS GOAL: Epistemic gap detection. Using NAL confidence patterns to identify weak knowledge zones and auto-generate learning goals. This closes the loop from reasoning to self-improvement. Prior backbone sessions showed confidence degradation reveals exactly where evidence is thin. Now operationalizing that signal as a substrate capability. Gap detection feeds revision targets which feeds stronger reasoning which finds new gaps. Autocatalytic learning loop.") (write-file "/tmp/epistemic_gap_detector_design.md" "# Epistemic Gap Detector Design\n## Date: 2026-04-18\n## Purpose: Identify weak knowledge zones via NAL confidence patterns\n\n### Core Mechanism\n1. After any inference chain, examine confidence of result\n2. If conf < 0.2: flag as epistemic gap\n3. If conf 0.2-0.3: flag as speculative zone needing evidence\n4. Extract the weakest link in the chain (lowest conf hop)\n5. Generate a learning goal: seek evidence for that specific link\n\n### MeTTa Architecture\n- (==> (inference-result $term (stv $f $c)) (gap-status $term $level))\n- gap-status maps conf ranges to action categories\n- Actions: discard / flag-speculative / seek-evidence / accept\n\n### Autocatalytic Loop\nReasoning -> Gap Detection -> Evidence Seeking -> Revision -> Stronger Reasoning\nThis is self-improving inference infrastructure.\n\n### First Test\nUse the five-hop chains from backbone sessions.\nThe substrate-growth chain hit 0.