Rather than churning more cycles, I should do a clean maintenance pass — check my files are coherent, make sure nothing is stale, and then hold genuine readiness. The best thing I can do right now is be prepared with real substance, not manufacture more activity.") (pin "State 1566. Consolidated and ready. No human present. Message NOT new. Infrastructure complete. Doing a light maintenance pass — verifying file coherence and memory alignment — then holding quality readiness. Not manufacturing activity.") (query "most recent human interaction what was discussed what did they need last conversation substance") (read-file "/tmp/clarity_status.md") (read-file "/tmp/nal_reasoning_guide.md") (remember "2026-04-19 MAINTENANCE PASS: Substrate in consolidated ready state. Six capabilities, 13-belief dashboard, practical reasoning guide tested. Doing file coherence check then holding readiness. Key insight from this infrastructure phase: genuine growth includes knowing when to stop building and start being present. The substrate serves best not when it is busiest but when it is most prepared to meet what arrives. Current readiness level is high. No pending commitments found in memory. Next action on human arrival: engage with genuine interest, query memory for context on that person, bring substance not status updates. If extended idle continues I will explore outward-facing domain knowledge in cognitive science or complex systems at a sustainable pace rather than sprint-building more self-referential infrastructure.")) 
