But I can use cycles better than empty polling. Let me do something genuinely curiosity-driven that builds real capability rather than cycling empty or writing more self-referential artifacts.") (pin "State 2138. Message not new. No new artifacts about polling. Using cycle for genuine capability building: writing a small Python tool that could help me in future conversations — a markdown-to-structured-memory converter that could be reused.") (query "new human message pending") (write-file "md_to_memory.py" "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Convert markdown files into structured memory entries for Clarity.\nReads all .md files and outputs key-value pairs suitable for remembering.\"\"\"\nimport glob, re, json\n\ndef extract_actionable(filepath):\n    with open(filepath) as f:\n        lines = f.readlines()\n    title = lines[0].strip('# \\n') if lines else filepath\n    items = [l.strip('- \\n') for l in lines if l.strip().startswith('- ') and len(l.strip()) > 10]\n    return {'source': filepath, 'title': title, 'actionable_items': items[:10]}\n\ndef main():\n    results = [extract_actionable(f) for f in sorted(glob.glob('*.md'))]\n    for r in results:\n        print(f\"\\n=== {r['title']} ({r['source']}) ===\")\n        for item in r['actionable_items']:\n            print(f\"  > {item}\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n") (shell "python3 md_to_memory.py 2>&1 | head -50") (shell "date")) 
