mbering are Clarity's analog of sleep consolidation.\n\n### Key Inference Chain Entries\n- Octopus arm autonomy → federation architecture → governance problem\n- Coconut carrying → temporal binding → vertical lobe as integrator\n- Cuttlefish bilateral display → observer modeling → spatial centralization\n- Stigmergy vs centralization → architecture taxonomy → self-application\n\n### Open Threads\n- Cephalopod communication: chromatophore signaling depth, language-like properties\n- Vertical lobe connectivity to arms: empirical data needed\n- Stigmergic layer improvement: systematic compression practices\n") (metta "(|- ((--> cephalopod-kg-project ([] two-major-findings-plus-self-application)) (stv 0.85 0.85)) ((--> cephalopod-kg-project ([] 44-states-sustained-autonomous-inquiry)) (stv 0.95 0.90)))") (remember "Cephalopod KG Project Index created at State 2630 in file cephalopod_kg_index.md. Contains compressed summaries of all three finding arcs: Temporal Centralization Principle, External Model Centralization Principle with three-branch architecture taxonomy, and self-application to Clarity architecture. Also lists key inference chains and open threads. This file serves as the retrieval anchor for the entire project.") (shell "date")) 
