((pin "State 2633. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Awaiting reply — attentive given urgent person-state. Cephalopod project 47 states. New sub-arc: chromatophore signaling — indexical vs compositional structure.") (query "cephalopod chromatophore signaling communication compositional language") (metta "(|- ((--> cuttlefish-chromatophore-displays ([] fixed-repertoire-of-patterns)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] fixed-repertoire-of-patterns)) (--> $1 ([] indexical-not-compositional))) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (metta "(|- ((--> cuttlefish-chromatophore-displays ([] context-dependent-pattern-selection)) (stv 0.85 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] context-dependent-pattern-selection)) (--> $1 ([] pragmatic-competence-without-syntax))) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2633 - Chromatophore Signaling: Indexical vs Compositional?\n- Core question: do cephalopod visual displays have compositional structure (combine elements to create new meanings) or are they a fixed repertoire of holistic signals?\n- Evidence toward indexical: cuttlefish displays seem to be whole-body patterns selected from a repertoire — threat, courtship, camouflage, submission. Each is a complete gestalt, not built from combinable parts.\n- Evidence toward something more: the bilateral asymmetric display (State 2622) shows that patterns CAN be independently controlled on different body regions simultaneously. This is spatial independence if not compositionality.\n- Key distinction: compositionality requires that parts have stable meanings that combine systematically. Does a stripe on the left side MEAN something independent of a spot on the right?\n- Probably not in the linguistic sense. But there may be pragmatic compositionality — the COMBINATION of courtship-left + male-coloring-right achieves a communicative goal neither achieves alone.\n- This is closer to pragmatic competence without syntax: knowing what to display to whom, without a grammar.\n- Analogy: human gesture is pragmatically rich but not compositional in the way speech is. Cephalopod signaling may be gesture-like.\n- The bilateral display is remarkable not because it is language but because it demonstrates audience-specific pragmatics — a capacity usually thought to require theory of mind.\n- Revised position: cephalopod communication is indexical in structure but pragmatic in deployment. The sophistication is in the USE, not the CODE.\n- This maps onto the centralization finding: pattern generation (code) is distributed/local, but pattern deployment (pragmatics) requires centralized observer-modeling.\n- Next: is there any evidence of novel pattern generation — displays not seen before, created for new situations? That would push toward productivity, a key language property.\n")) 
