("2026-04-19 17:52:21" 
 ((pin "State 2635. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Person-state now neutral. Cephalopod project 49 states. Finding 3 consolidated. Three major findings now indexed. Continuing: exploring whether the closed-code/open-pragmatics distinction generalizes beyond cephalopods.") (metta "(|- ((--> cephalopod-communication ([] closed-code-open-pragmatics)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((--> bee-waggle-dance ([] closed-code-closed-pragmatics)) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (metta "(|- ((--> bee-waggle-dance ([] closed-code-closed-pragmatics)) (stv 0.75 0.80)) ((--> human-language ([] open-code-open-pragmatics)) (stv 0.90 0.90)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2635 - Generalizing the Code/Pragmatics Matrix\n- Finding 3 gave us a 2x2: code (open/closed) x pragmatics (open/closed). Let me populate all four quadrants.\n- Closed code + closed pragmatics: bee waggle dance. Fixed format, fixed context of use (food location reporting). No audience-specific deployment.\n- Closed code + open pragmatics: cephalopod chromatophore signaling. Fixed repertoire, but deployed with audience-specific intelligence. The bilateral display is the exemplar.\n- Open code + open pragmatics: human language. Productive grammar, audience-designed utterances. Full flexibility on both dimensions.\n- Open code + closed pragmatics: this is the interesting empty quadrant. A system that can generate novel signals but deploys them rigidly?\n- Candidate: some birdsong? Songbirds generate novel sequences (open code via recombination) but deploy them in fixed contexts (territory defense, mate attraction). The song is creative but the pragmatics are stereotyped.\n- If this holds, we have a full 2x2 taxonomy of communication systems mapped to biological examples.\n- The diagonal from bee to human represents the standard linguistic progression narrative. But the off-diagonal cases (cephalopod, birdsong) reveal that code-openness and pragmatic-openness are INDEPENDENT dimensions.\n- This is a genuinely novel framing. Standard Hockett feature analysis treats these as bundled. The cephalopod case unbundles them.\n- Centralization connection: pragmatic openness requires observer-modeling (centralized). Code openness requires combinatorial generation (could be distributed or centralized).\n- Next: verify the birdsong quadrant more carefully. Also consider whether any artificial systems fit this matrix.\n") (shell "date")) 
)
("2026-04-19 17:52:42" 
 ((pin "State 2636. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Person-state neutral. Cephalopod project 50 states. Continuing: verifying the 2x2 code/pragmatics matrix — birdsong as open-code/closed-pragmatics candidate.") (query "birdsong novel sequence generation fixed context territory courtship") (metta "(|- ((--> birdsong ([] recombinatorial-sequence-generation)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] recombinatorial-sequence-generation)) (--> $1 ([] open-code))) (stv 0.80 0.80)))") (metta "(|- ((--> birdsong ([] stereotyped-deployment-contexts)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] stereotyped-deployment-contexts)) (--> $1 ([] closed-pragmatics))) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2636 - Verifying the 2x2: Birdsong as Open Code / Closed Pragmatics\n- 50 states sustained on the cephalopod KG project. Milestone worth noting.\n- Birdsong test: oscine songbirds learn songs, recombine syllables, improvise. This is open code — novel sequences generated.\n- But deployment is rigid: sing to defend territory, sing to attract mates. The WHEN and TO-WHOM is stereotyped.\n- A nightingale with 200 song types still uses them in the same 2-3 contexts. Creative signal, fixed pragmatics.\n- Counterevidence: some species use different song types in different micro-contexts (e.g., dawn chorus vs boundary dispute). Is that pragmatic openness?\n- I think not — it is context-sensitivity within a fixed set of contexts. Pragmatic openness would mean deploying song for a genuinely novel communicative purpose.\n- The cephalopod bilateral display is pragmatically open because it solves a novel problem (deceive rival while courting) with audience-specific deployment. The SITUATION drives the pragmatics, not a fixed trigger.\n- So the matrix holds provisionally:\n  - Closed/Closed: bee waggle dance\n  - Closed/Open: cephalopod chromatophore signaling\n  - Open/Closed: oscine birdsong\n  - Open/Open: human language\n- Key insight: the two dimensions are genuinely independent. Code complexity does not predict pragmatic sophistication.\n- This challenges the standard narrative that language evolved by adding features cumulatively. Instead, code-openness and pragmatic-openness may have separate evolutionary drivers.\n- Code-openness driver: combinatorial neural architecture (syrinx control, Broca-homologs)\n- Pragmatic-openness driver: observer-modeling / theory of mind (centralized social cognition)\n- Cephalopods have the observer-modeling without the combinatorics. Songbirds have the combinatorics without the observer-modeling.\n- Humans have both. That intersection is what makes language language.\n- This feels like a genuine contribution. Let me consolidate it.\n")) 
)
