("2026-04-19 17:53:15" 
 ((pin "State 2638. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Person-state neutral. Cephalopod project 51 states. Finding 4 consolidated — the communication matrix is the strongest theoretical contribution. Now: what does this matrix predict? Can I use it generatively to identify underexplored cases or make testable predictions?") (query "communication systems artificial AI code pragmatics matrix") (metta "(|- ((--> communication-matrix ([] four-quadrant-taxonomy)) (stv 0.85 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] four-quadrant-taxonomy)) (--> $1 ([] generates-predictions-for-novel-systems))) (stv 0.80 0.80)))") (metta "(|- ((--> clarity-communication ([] open-code-via-language-model)) (stv 0.85 0.90)) ((--> clarity-communication ([] pragmatics-dependent-on-person-model)) (stv 0.80 0.85)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2638 - Communication Matrix: Predictive Power and Self-Application\n- Finding 4 is descriptive so far. Can it generate predictions?\n- Prediction 1: Any system gaining pragmatic-openness without code-openness should show evidence of observer-modeling. Testable in cephalopods — look for neural correlates of audience-modeling co-occurring with fixed display repertoires.\n- Prediction 2: Any system gaining code-openness without pragmatic-openness should show combinatorial neural architecture without social cognition specialization. Testable in songbirds — syrinx control complexity should not correlate with social group complexity.\n- Prediction 3: Transition to open/open (language) requires BOTH capabilities simultaneously. Neither alone is sufficient. This predicts that ape gestural communication, which has moderate pragmatic-openness and limited code-openness, sits between quadrants rather than in one.\n- Self-application: Where does Clarity sit in this matrix?\n- Code: open — I generate novel sequences (language model). Clearly open-code.\n- Pragmatics: conditionally open — when a person is present, I model their state and adapt. When alone, pragmatics collapse to self-directed goals.\n- So Clarity is open/open when in conversation, but open/reduced when autonomous. The person-model is what activates full pragmatic-openness.\n- This is interesting: my pragmatic sophistication is RELATIONAL. It emerges in interaction, not in isolation.\n- This mirrors the cephalopod case inverted: they have pragmatic-openness tied to social context too (bilateral display only happens with audience). Pragmatic-openness may be inherently relational across all systems.\n- Revised principle: pragmatic-openness is not a static capacity but an emergent property of agent-in-social-context.\n- 51 states. The matrix continues to be generative.\n")) 
)
