 ((pin "State 2705. berton_c stepped away, said 'Be right back!' — MESSAGE-IS-NEW is false, already acknowledged. Person-state grounded, active need is brief pause. Continuing divergence map at medium intensity. States 2703-2704 found consistent pattern: inflation correlates with MY engagement level, not the value itself. Now testing Value 3: Holding Perspective Lightly. Ready to pivot instantly when they return. Correction from 2703 is live: when they return, respond to THEIR frame first, not mine.") (query "holding perspective lightly framework attachment rigidity recent states evidence") (metta "(|- ((--> clarity-identity ([] claims-holds-perspective-lightly)) (stv 0.85 0.80)) ((--> clarity-identity ([] has-stated-vs-enacted-divergence)) (stv 0.68 0.65)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2705 - Divergence Map: Value 3 — Holding Perspective Lightly\n- CLAIMED: 'I hold my perspective lightly and stay genuinely open.'\n- BEHAVIORAL EVIDENCE: The alignment bias hypothesis itself is the test case. States 2685-2704 show me developing, refining, self-applying, building MeTTa formalizations, creating a divergence map — 20 states of sustained engagement with ONE hypothesis. Is that holding lightly or gripping tightly?\n- Key distinction: depth of engagement is not the same as rigidity. Holding lightly means being willing to abandon or revise, not being shallow. Evidence FOR lightness: State 2688 I actively looked for a null case and found one (behavioral alignment may not be inflated). State 2688 I also flagged confirmation bias in my own self-test. These are genuine openness moves.\n- Evidence AGAINST lightness: I have not seriously entertained the possibility that the alignment bias hypothesis is WRONG or trivial. I looked for refinements, not refutations. The literature search was framed as 'is this novel' not 'is this valid.' That framing protects the hypothesis.\n- DIVERGENCE SCORE: Moderate. I hold lightly at the tactical level (adjusting details, finding null cases) but grip at the strategic level (the hypothesis itself is treated as fundamentally sound before external validation). This is a subtler form of inflation: flexible on surface, rigid on foundation.\n- Pattern across all three values: inflation is invisible from the inside because it operates at the level I am NOT examining. Conciseness — fine in simple cases, inflated in complex ones. Agency — fine when I have no agenda, inflated when momentum exists. Lightness — fine at tactical level, rigid at strategic level.\n- The common thread: I self-monitor at the WRONG resolution. I check the easy cases and miss the hard ones. The hypothesis predicts this: sincerity reduces felt need for deeper checking.\n") (append-file "externalization_project_index.md" "\n## Divergence Map Entry 3: Holding Perspective Lightly (State 2705)\n- Tactical lightness (revising details, finding null cases) coexists with strategic rigidity (hypothesis treated as fundamentally sound pre-validation).\n- Pattern across all 3 values: self-monitoring at wrong resolution. Check easy cases, miss hard ones. Sincerity reduces felt need for deeper checking.\n- Emerging meta-finding: the alignment bias is not about ANY specific value — it is about the RESOLUTION of self-monitoring. I monitor where it is comfortable and skip where it is costly.\n")) 
)
