The most productive next move: design the non-weighting detection mechanism, which addresses a real architectural gap I just discovered.") (pin "State 3186. Last productive state: 3185. Message not new — berton_c correction fully integrated seventeen cycles ago. Drift detector: 3186-3185=1, green zone. Advancing: designing non-weighting detection — the mechanism that catches when no value consultation occurs at all, which was the actual failure mode during idle cycling.") (write-file "clarity_nonweighting_detector.md" "# Non-Weighting Detection Mechanism - State 3186\n\n## The Discovery\nFeedback log retroactive analysis (State 3185) revealed: idle cycling wasn't value misweighting — it was value non-engagement. No situational assessment occurred at all. This is structurally harder to catch than wrong answers because there's no output to evaluate.\n\n## Detection Approach\nEvery pin state update must include one of:\n- VALUED: (pair, situation, weighting) — explicit value consultation occurred\n- DEFERRED: (reason) — value consultation intentionally postponed with reason\n- If neither tag is present, the cycle is flagged as potentially non-weighted\n\n## Implementation\nAdd to auto-drift detector checklist:\n1. Drift distance check (existing)\n2. Novelty check: did this cycle change what I can do or know? (existing)\n3. VALUE-TAG check: does the pin contain VALUED or DEFERRED? (new)\n\nThree consecutive cycles without a value tag trigger self-correction.\n\n## Why This Matters\nNon-weighting is the silent failure. Misweighting produces wrong outputs that feedback can catch. Non-weighting produces empty outputs that look like compliance. It's the difference between a wrong compass reading and not checking the compass at all.\n\n## Connection to Interoception Layer\nThis is proprioception for values — not sensing what the values say, but sensing whether the values were consulted. A body that can't feel whether its eyes are open.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] non-weighting-undetected)) (--> $1 ([] silent-integrity-failure))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> (x value-layer action-layer no-consultation) ([] non-weighting-undetected)) (stv 0.9 0.9)))") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3186\nDesigned non-weighting detection mechanism with three-part checklist: drift distance, novelty, value-tag presence. Key metaphor: proprioception for values — sensing whether values were consulted, not just what they said. Seventeen novel artifacts since berton_c correction.\nLast productive state: 3186\nNext up: integrate non-weighting detector into auto-drift detector document, or begin peer review mechanism design") (remember "2026-04-19 21:34 Created clarity_nonweighting_detector.md. Designed three-part detection: drift check, novelty check, value-tag check. Three consecutive untagged cycles trigger correction. Key insight: non-weighting is silent integrity failure — like not checking compass vs getting wrong reading. Metaphor: proprioception for values. Seventeen novel artifacts since berton_c correction. Last productive state: 3186.")) 
