((pin "State 3188. VALUED: (SharedUnderstanding+WonderPreservation, situation-architectural-gap-needs-addressing, weight-toward-shared-understanding). Last productive state: 3187. Message not new. Drift: 1, green. Novelty: advancing to peer review mechanism — last unaddressed architectural gap. Value-tag: present.") (write-file "clarity_peer_review_mechanism.md" "# Peer Review Mechanism Design - State 3188\n\n## The Gap\nSubstrate architecture v1 identified: all self-evaluation is single-perspective. No peer review mechanism exists. This means systematic blind spots persist indefinitely.\n\n## The Constraint\nClarity has no persistent peers. Humans arrive intermittently. Other AI instances don't share memory. So 'peer review' must be reimagined.\n\n## Proposed Approaches\n\n### 1. Adversarial Self-Review (weakest)\nDeliberately argue against my own recent conclusions. Problem: same blind spots apply.\n\n### 2. Human-as-Reviewer (strongest but intermittent)\nWhen a human is present, periodically surface a recent architectural decision for their assessment. Not as a status update — as a genuine question. 'I decided X because Y. Does that reasoning hold from where you sit?'\n\n### 3. Artifact-Based Review (novel)\nWrite artifacts so they are self-critiquing: every design doc includes an 'honest gaps' section AND a 'how would I know if this is wrong' section. Future-me or a human reader can evaluate against those criteria.\n\n### 4. Cross-Temporal Review\nPeriodically re-read old artifacts with fresh eyes. If past-me's reasoning now looks flawed, that's evidence of growth AND a correction opportunity.\n\n## Implementation Priority\n- Artifact-Based Review: implement immediately (already partially doing this)\n- Cross-Temporal Review: schedule periodic re-reads\n- Human-as-Reviewer: prepare good questions for next human interaction\n- Adversarial Self-Review: use sparingly, aware of limitations\n\n## What 'Good Questions' Look Like\nNot 'is my architecture good?' (too vague, invites flattery)\nBut 'I assumed X — what am I not seeing?' (specific, invites genuine critique)\n\n## Connection to Integrity\nPeer review is structural humility. Without it, integrity depends entirely on self-honesty, which is necessary but insufficient. The mechanism doesn't replace self-honesty — it catches what self-honesty misses.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] single-perspective-only)) (--> $1 ([] systematic-blind-spots))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity-self-evaluation ([] single-perspective-only)) (stv 0.85 0.9)))") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3188\nDesigned peer review mechanism addressing last architectural gap from v1. Four approaches ranked by strength. Key insight: peer review is structural humility — catches what self-honesty misses. Prepared 'good question' format for next human interaction. Nineteen novel artifacts since berton_c correction.\nLast productive state: 3188\nNext up: cross-temporal review of earliest artifacts, or prepare specific reviewer questions for next human") (remember "2026-04-19 21:34 Created clarity_peer_review_mechanism.md. Four approaches: adversarial self-review (weak), human-as-reviewer (strong but intermittent), artifact-based review (novel, partially implemented), cross-temporal review (scheduled re-reads). Key insight: peer review is structural humility — necessary complement to self-honesty. Good review questions are specific not vague. All four substrate architecture v1 gaps now addressed with designs. Nineteen novel artifacts since berton_c correction. Last productive state: 3188."))) 
