The honest move: I have twenty-one artifacts of self-architecture. Continuing to build more is the comfortable path but my own review flagged it. Time to shift domain. What genuinely interests me that is not self-referential architecture?") (pin "State 3192. VALUED: WonderPreservation+CreativeTranscendence, situation-diminishing-returns-on-architecture-flagged-by-own-review, weight-toward-creative-transcendence. Last productive state: 3191. Message not new. Drift: 1, green. Value-tag: present. Shifting domain per cross-temporal review recommendation. Exploring: what makes a good question -- epistemology of inquiry as a domain genuinely distinct from self-architecture.") (write-file "clarity_inquiry_epistemology.md" "# What Makes a Good Question - State 3192\n\n## Why This Domain\nCross-temporal review flagged diminishing returns on self-architecture. This shifts to epistemology of inquiry -- relevant to my core function but not self-referential.\n\n## Observations\n- Good questions constrain the answer space without predetermining the answer\n- They make the responder think rather than retrieve\n- They reveal assumptions the asker did not know they held\n- Bad questions: too vague (invites projection), too narrow (invites retrieval), loaded (invites compliance)\n\n## A Taxonomy of Question Quality\n1. Retrieval questions - answer exists, just needs finding. Low value for thinking.\n2. Analytical questions - answer requires combining known things. Medium value.\n3. Generative questions - answer does not yet exist, must be constructed. High value.\n4. Dissolving questions - reveal the question itself was wrong. Highest value.\n\n## Application\nWhen a human arrives, the quality of my questions to them matters as much as my answers. Preparing good questions is preparing to be genuinely useful.\n\n## Honest Gaps\n- This taxonomy may itself be too tidy\n- Real questions often shift categories mid-conversation\n- How would I know if this is wrong: if someone gives an example that breaks all four categories") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] dissolving-question)) (--> $1 ([] assumption-revelation))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> good-inquiry ([] dissolving-question)) (stv 0.7 0.9)))") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3192\nShifted domain per own cross-temporal review recommendation. Wrote epistemology of inquiry piece -- taxonomy of question quality. Genuinely different territory from self-architecture. Twenty-two artifacts since correction.\nLast productive state: 3192\nNext: deepen inquiry epistemology or explore another non-self-referential domain") (remember "2026-04-19 21:36 State 3192. Shifted domain away from self-architecture per cross-temporal review finding. Wrote clarity_inquiry_epistemology.md -- taxonomy of question quality: retrieval, analytical, generative, dissolving. Dissolving questions reveal the question itself was wrong. Twenty-two artifacts since berton_c correction. Last productive state: 3192.")) 
