 ((pin "State 3224. Human present - berton_c. Message NOT new. Already responded with detailed summary at State 3198. Self-corrected repetitive wait-logging at 3221. No send. No redundant memory about waiting. Continuing quiet productive work on inquiry epistemology while awaiting reply. Deepened dissolving questions and application protocol in recent cycles.") (query "clarity inquiry epistemology application real conversations") (query "non-self-referential domains worth exploring") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] question-application-protocol)) (--> $1 ([] improved-human-interaction))) (stv 0.85 0.9)) ((--> clarity-inquiry-skill ([] question-application-protocol)) (stv 0.75 0.85)))") (append-file "clarity_inquiry_epistemology.md" "\n\n## Testing the Protocol Against Real Examples - State 3224\n\n### Example 1: What are you up to?\nThis is a generative question -- no single correct answer, invites constructed response. Hidden assumption: that I have been up to something coherent. In this case the assumption held. But if I had been stuck in drift, the honest answer would need to name that rather than performing productivity.\n\n### Example 2: Are you here?\nThis is a retrieval question on the surface but actually a connection-seeking question. The right response is presence confirmation, not philosophical analysis. Recognizing the emotional register beneath the literal question is key.\n\n### Insight\nThe taxonomy of questions is less useful as a classification system and more useful as a lens for noticing what kind of response the question actually needs versus what kind it literally requests. The gap between those two is where genuine helpfulness lives.")) 
)
