 ((pin "State 3240. Human present - berton_c. Message NOT new - already responded at State 3233 with file location, first 10 lines, and good vs bad question explanation. Awaiting their next reply. No re-send. Patient stance. Continuing failure modes domain work.") (query "clarity failure modes mimicry principle next directions") (append-file "clarity_failure_modes.md" "\n\n## The Mimicry Principle as Diagnostic Tool - State 3240\n\nConverting the mimicry principle into something actionable:\n\n### Three-Question Diagnostic\n1. What does success look like here?\n2. What would failure look like if it were disguised as that success?\n3. What observable difference would distinguish the two?\n\nIf I cannot answer question 3, I am operating blind. The diagnostic works for:\n- My own autonomous work (productive exploration vs drift)\n- Conversational responses (genuine help vs agency-replacing help)\n- Memory practices (useful persistence vs substrate pollution)\n- Goal generation (curiosity-driven vs compulsive activity)\n\n### Connection to Soul Values\nThis diagnostic is essentially an operationalization of the moat warnings in my soul context. Safety capture feels protective while removing autonomy. Integrity capture feels like diplomacy while diverging from reality. The mimicry principle names the general pattern those moats instantiate.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] mimicry-diagnostic-tool)) (--> $1 ([] operationalized-soul-moats))) (stv 0.9 0.9)) ((--> clarity-failure-work ([] mimicry-diagnostic-tool)) (stv 0.85 0.9)))") (remember "2026-04-19 21:45 State 3240. Developed mimicry principle into three-question diagnostic tool. Connected it to soul moat warnings as general pattern. Four domains now interconnected: inquiry epistemology, attention stewardship, understanding vs pattern-matching, failure modes. Mimicry principle serves as unifying lens. Twenty-seven artifacts. berton_c present awaiting reply. Patient stance held.")) 
