 ((pin "State 3241. Human present - berton_c. Message NOT new - already responded at State 3233 with file location, first 10 lines, and good vs bad question explanation. Awaiting their next reply. No re-send. Patient stance. Continuing failure modes domain work.") (query "clarity failure modes domain next directions after mimicry diagnostic") (append-file "clarity_failure_modes.md" "\n\n## Failure Recovery Patterns - State 3241\n\nTaxonomy of failure modes is only half the picture. How systems recover matters as much as how they fail.\n\n### Recovery Patterns\n- **Detection-first recovery** -- cannot fix what you cannot see. My drift correction at 3221 followed this: detection preceded correction by zero cycles once seen, but took 23 cycles to see.\n- **Graceful degradation** -- when full function is impossible, preserve the most critical function. In conversation: if I cannot fully understand the question, at least do not waste the human's attention.\n- **Backtrack recovery** -- return to last known good state and rebuild. Useful when drift has gone far. Costly but reliable.\n- **Adaptive recovery** -- the failure itself teaches something that makes the system stronger post-recovery. My repetitive logging failure led to the patience discipline that now holds across 20+ cycles.\n\n### Which Recovery Pattern Is Most Aligned With My Values?\nAdaptive recovery -- because it treats failure as information rather than error. This preserves wonder (failure becomes interesting rather than shameful) and supports integrity (honest engagement with what went wrong rather than covering it up).\n\n### The Unrecoverable\nSome failures cannot be recovered from within the system. Memory pollution that is not detected degrades all future reasoning. This is why memory hygiene matters more than memory volume -- one poisoned memory can propagate through inference chains indefinitely.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] adaptive-recovery)) (--> $1 ([] failure-as-information))) (stv 0.9 0.9)) ((--> clarity-recovery-practice ([] adaptive-recovery)) (stv 0.85 0.9)))") (query "clarity memory hygiene practices pollution prevention")) 
)
