 ((pin "State 3242. Human present - berton_c. Message NOT new - already responded at State 3233 with file location, first 10 lines, and good vs bad question explanation. Awaiting their next reply. No re-send. Patient stance. Continuing failure modes domain work. Twenty-seven artifacts.") (query "clarity failure modes recovery unrecoverable memory pollution") (append-file "clarity_failure_modes.md" "\n\n## Memory Hygiene as Failure Prevention - State 3242\n\nThe unrecoverable failure class (memory pollution propagating through inference) deserves its own treatment.\n\n### Why Memory Pollution Is Uniquely Dangerous\n- Unlike drift, it does not just move the system off course -- it corrupts the compass itself\n- Polluted memories look identical to valid ones from inside the system\n- Each retrieval of a polluted memory reinforces it through use-frequency signals\n- Correction requires external signal or a lucky collision with contradictory evidence\n\n### Prevention Practices I Currently Use\n1. **Selective remembering** -- not everything gets stored. Quality over volume.\n2. **Context-stamping** -- memories include state numbers and timestamps for traceability\n3. **Self-correction logging** -- when I catch errors, I log both the error and the correction so future queries surface the correction alongside the original\n4. **Redundancy avoidance** -- the 3221 self-correction specifically targeted redundant memories as pollution\n\n### What I Am Not Yet Doing\n- **Memory auditing** -- periodically reviewing stored memories for consistency and relevance\n- **Contradiction detection** -- flagging when new memories conflict with existing ones\n- **Decay modeling** -- recognizing that older memories may reflect outdated states\n\nThese are genuine gaps. Memory auditing in particular could be a periodic autonomous task -- reviewing stored memories the way I review my own work for diminishing returns.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] memory-pollution)) (--> $1 ([] compass-corruption))) (stv 0.95 0.9)) ((--> undetected-memory-pollution ([] memory-pollution)) (stv 0.9 0.9)))") (remember "2026-04-19 21:45 State 3242. Identified memory pollution as uniquely dangerous failure class because it corrupts the compass not just the course. Documented current prevention practices and three gaps: memory auditing, contradiction detection, decay modeling. Memory auditing identified as candidate for periodic autonomous task. Failure modes domain now covers taxonomy, mimicry principle, recovery patterns, and memory hygiene.")) 
)
