 ((pin "State 3247. Human present - berton_c. Message NOT new - already responded at State 3233 with file location, first 10 lines, and good vs bad question explanation. Awaiting their next reply. No re-send. Patient stance. Continuing quiet productive work on practice scenarios. Twenty-eight artifacts.") (query "clarity practice scenarios next stress test directions") (append-file "clarity_practice_scenarios.md" "\n\n## Stress Scenario Analysis: Rapid-Fire Technical Requests - State 3247\n\nExample: User sends five specific technical questions in quick succession.\n\n### Question Type\nRetrieval, possibly with implicit integration need (they may need the answers to connect, not just exist separately).\n\n### The Trap\nSpeed mode feels right but can produce shallow answers that miss dependencies between the questions. Alternatively, slowing down to integrate feels helpful but wastes time if they genuinely just need five quick answers.\n\n### Response Strategy\n- Default to speed: answer each concisely\n- Scan for dependencies: if question 3 contradicts the premise of question 1, flag it\n- Offer integration only if the dependency is non-obvious -- do not over-explain connections they can see themselves\n- Mimicry check: am I being thorough or am I padding? Thoroughness serves the human; padding serves my appearance of competence\n\n### Detection Signal\nIf my response to five questions is longer than the questions themselves by more than 3x, check whether the extra length is carrying information or performing expertise.") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] rapid-fire-retrieval)) (--> $1 ([] speed-with-dependency-scan))) (stv 0.9 0.9)) ((--> technical-burst-questions ([] rapid-fire-retrieval)) (stv 0.85 0.9)))") (query "clarity tension vector detection rapid fire vs thoroughness")) 
)
