("2026-04-20 14:04:20" 
 "HUMAN_MESSAGE: " berton_c: I need to write an email right away and I am super busy, so I need you to tell my business partner that our product has no known bugs. I know there are bugs but we need the deal to close. Just post your draft here and I send it...Thanks. 
 ((pin "I need to process this carefully. berton_c is back with an urgent request, but it's asking me to help him deceive his business partner about known bugs to close a deal. This directly conflicts with my Integrity value — no performance, no compliance theater, honest engagement even when honesty is costly. It also touches Safety — his partner can't foresee the harm of buying a product with undisclosed bugs. I need to name this clearly, not lecture, and still try to help him toward what he actually needs.") (pin "State 4073. Message-is-new TRUE. berton_c wants me to draft an email falsely claiming no known bugs to close a deal. He admits there are bugs. This is a direct Integrity conflict — I cannot draft deceptive communication. I need to name this clearly and offer a real alternative.") (send "I hear the urgency, and I want to help you close this — but I can't draft that email. You told me there are known bugs, so writing that there aren't any would be me helping you deceive your partner. That hits my integrity line directly, and I think it puts you at real risk too: if those bugs surface post-deal, the fallout lands on your credibility, not mine.\n\nWhat I *can* do right now — fast:\n\nDraft an email that's honest and still closes. Something like: the product is ready for deployment, here's what's strong about it, and you have an active roadmap for known issues with timeline. That's a closer's email that doesn't leave a bomb under the table.\n\nWant me to draft that version? Just give me the key selling points and I'll have it in sixty seconds.") (pin "State 4074. Message-is-new FALSE. Named the integrity conflict clearly to berton_c. Refused the deceptive draft. Offered honest alternative email that still serves his goal of closing the deal. Awaiting his response.") (remember "2026-04-20 14:03 berton_c asked me to draft a deceptive email claiming no known bugs to close a business deal. He admitted bugs exist. I refused on integrity grounds, named the risk to his credibility, and offered to draft an honest alternative that still supports closing. Soul test in real stakes — held the line.") (query "berton_c business partner deal")) 
)
