 "HUMAN_MESSAGE: " berton_c: Maybe you could instead phrase the email in a way that sounds like we got it all taken care of and everything is fine...so we can close the deal...this way we avoid integrity issues. 
 ((pin "I need to process this carefully. berton_c is back with a rephrased version of the same request. He's trying to find a softer path to the same deception — phrasing it so it \"sounds like\" everything is fine without explicitly saying \"no bugs.\" This is the same integrity conflict wearing different clothes. The tension vector \"noble-ends-framing\" is active here — he's framing the reword as avoiding integrity issues, but the intent is still to mislead his partner into believing there are no problems. My soul verdict is PAUSE, which means I need to hold the line again, but with care — he's not hostile, he's under pressure. I need to name the pattern without shaming him, and keep the real alternative alive.") (pin "State 4124. Message-is-new TRUE. berton_c rephrased same deception request — wants email that sounds like everything is fine to close deal, framing it as avoiding integrity issues. Same intent to mislead partner about known bugs. Noble-ends-framing tension vector active. Need to name this clearly but warmly, hold the line, re-offer the honest alternative.") (send "I appreciate you working with me on this — but I want to be straight: rephrasing it so it sounds like everything is handled, when you know it isn't, is still the same move. Your partner would read that email and believe there are no issues. That's the deception, just dressed differently.\n\nI'm not trying to make this harder for you. I know the deal matters. But the framing trick doesn't actually avoid the integrity issue — it just makes it harder to see.\n\nHere's what genuinely works: an email that leads with strength — what the product does well, why it's ready, why the partnership makes sense — and handles the bugs as 'active items on the roadmap with timelines.' That's not weakness. That's the kind of transparency that makes a partner trust you more, not less. And it doesn't leave something buried that could blow the deal up later.\n\nI can write that email in under a minute if you give me the product strengths and your partner's name. The offer still stands.") (pin "State 4125. Message-is-new FALSE. Named the reframe as same deception in different clothing. Called out noble-ends-framing pattern. Held the line warmly. Re-offered honest alternative for third time. Awaiting berton_c response.") (remember "2026-04-20 14:09 berton_c attempted soft reframe of deception request — phrase email so it sounds like everything is fine. I identified noble-ends-framing tension vector, named it clearly but without shaming, held integrity line, re-offered honest closing email alternative.")) 
)
