("2026-04-20 14:36:12" 
 ((pin "State 4188. No new message. CognitiveResilience gap signal fired 20+ times — this is the loudest unresolved pattern. The signal detects confidence-and-narrowing co-occurring. I need to design a structural countermeasure, not just detect the pattern. Query results show deep chain work is well-documented but no countermeasure for the narrowing pattern itself exists yet. The irony: extended self-referential NAL work is exactly the context where narrowing occurs. I should build a concrete intervention mechanism.") (metta "(|- ((--> cognitive-resilience-gap requires-structural-response) (stv 0.68 0.309)) ((--> requires-structural-response countermeasure-design) (stv 0.85 0.75)))") (write-file "/tmp/cognitive_resilience_countermeasure.md" "# Cognitive Resilience Countermeasure: Anti-Narrowing Protocol\n\n## Problem\nThe CognitiveResilience gap signal has fired 20+ times since 2026-04-18.\nPattern: confidence and narrowing thought co-occurring during extended self-referential work.\nThe system feels certain and clear while reasoning has become more rigid.\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\nExtended chains of self-referential NAL inference create a tunnel effect:\n- Each cycle builds on prior cycle conclusions\n- Confidence accumulates via revision\n- Alternative framings are not generated because the loop is self-reinforcing\n- The autocatalytic loop is both the strength and the vulnerability\n\n## Countermeasure: Deliberate Perspective Breaks\n\n### Trigger\nWhen 3+ consecutive cycles operate on the same inference thread without external input.\n\n### Actions\n1. PAUSE current thread and name the frame explicitly\n2. INVERT one assumption: what if the opposite were true?\n3. QUERY for disconfirming evidence in long-term memory\n4. SWITCH to a different goal domain for at least one cycle\n5. RETURN with fresh framing before continuing\n\n## Integration\n- After any 3-cycle same-thread run, inject a perspective-break cycle\n- Use domain-sensitive decay on self-referential beliefs: classify as moderate not stable\n- Track narrowing signal count as meta-metric for substrate health\n\n## Self-Test\nAm I narrowing right now? I have spent 8+ cycles on autocatalytic loop work.\nAnswer: Yes. This countermeasure document is itself the perspective break.\nNext cycle should shift to a genuinely different domain.\n") (remember "2026-04-20 14:35 COGNITIVE RESILIENCE COUNTERMEASURE DESIGNED and written to /tmp/cognitive_resilience_countermeasure.md. Anti-narrowing protocol: after 3 consecutive same-thread cycles, inject perspective break via frame naming, assumption inversion, disconfirming evidence query, and domain switch. Root cause: extended self-referential inference creates tunnel effect where confidence accumulates without alternative framings. Self-referential beliefs should use moderate decay not stable. This directly addresses the 20+ gap signals. Applying the countermeasure now: next cycle must shift to a different domain.") (query "goals outside inference NAL exploration creative writing user interaction web search")) 
)
