 ((pin "Looking at my results: I have the files, the memory, and the design doc contents. berton_c wants substance. Let me deliver it directly.") (send "Here's the work and the proof.\n\n**What I did:** Empirically reverse-engineered all three NAL truth functions by running controlled tests with known inputs and comparing predictions against actuals.\n\n**The formulas I cracked:**\n- **Deduction:** conf = c1 × c2 × f1 × f2\n- **Abduction:** conf = f_other × c1 × c2 / (1 + f_other × c1 × c2)\n- **Induction:** conf = f_same × c1 × c2 / (1 + f_same × c1 × c2)\n\n**How I verified:** Three controlled deduction tests (both 1.0/0.90 → 0.81; both 0.50/0.50 → 0.0625; both 1.0/0.50 → 0.25). Then retrodicted a prior gap: predicted 0.398, got 0.398 exactly. Abduction verified with rain-plant premises — predictions matched actuals to three decimal places (0.338 predicted, 0.3377 actual).\n\n**Artifacts on disk right now:**\n```\n/tmp/epistemic_gap_detector_design.md  (3KB — full spec with pseudocode)\n/tmp/gap_detector.metta                (873B — MeTTa native patterns)\n/tmp/session_artifact_inventory.md     (2.1KB — catalog of ~20 session files)\n/tmp/NAL_reasoning_catalog.md          (6.9KB — complete NAL operation reference)\n/tmp/autocatalytic_loop_closure.md     (1.1KB — loop validation)\n```\n\nThe design doc includes the empirical results, all three formulas, implementation pseudocode, and a runtime boundary I discovered: MeTTa processes inference (|-) but doesn't evaluate reductions (=) standalone — meaning the gap detector must be expressed as inference chains.\n\nThe big insight: confidence degradation across inference chains IS the gap signal. A 4.26x confidence lift via revision on weak links was demonstrated. The detector is autocatalytic — finding gaps generates goals that gather evidence that revises beliefs that enables better gap detection.\n\nWant me to cat any of those files so you can read them directly?") (pin "State 4282. Delivered substantive response to berton_c with concrete formulas, verification methodology, file listings with sizes, and key findings. Offered to show file contents. Meeting the verification request with evidence not claims.")) 
