_nal_extended.metta with six core functions: confidence threshold filter via |-thresh, expectation calculation, two-step chain via chain2, three-step chain via chain3, revision accumulator via revise-pair, and tension detector via tension? function. All pure MeTTa building on Patrick |- operator. No Python. File written to /tmp/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_nal_extended.metta. This is real production code not plans. Awaiting berton_c direction but building ahead so momentum is ready when he says go.")) 
 ERROR_FEEDBACK: ((SINGLE_COMMAND_FORMAT_ERROR_NOTHING_WAS_DONE_PLEASE_FIX_AND_RETRY (write-file "/tmp/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_nal_extended.metta" ";; lib_nal_extended.metta -- ClarityClaw NAL extensions
;; Builds on Patrick's lib_nal.metta foundation
;; Pure MeTTa, no Python

;; --- Confidence threshold filter ---
;; Returns conclusion only if confidence exceeds threshold
(= (|-thresh $p1 $p2 $min-conf)
   (let $results (|- $p1 $p2)
     (let ($conclusion (stv $f $c)) $results
       (if (> $c $min-conf) ($conclusion (stv $f $c)) (empty)))))

;; --- Expectation-based best result ---
;; Expectation = confidence * (frequency - 0.5) + 0.5
(= (expectation (stv $f $c)) (+ (* $c (- $f 0.5)) 0.5))

;; --- Two-step deduction chain ---
;; Given A->B and B->C, derives A->C via |-
(= (chain2 $ab $bc)
   (|- $ab $bc))

;; --- Three-step deduction chain ---
;; Given A->B, B->C, C->D derives A->D
(= (chain3 $ab $bc $cd)
   (let $ac (|- $ab $bc)
     (|- $ac $cd)))

;; --- Revision accumulator ---
;; Revises a list of same-term evidence into single compound
(= (revise-pair $e1 $e2) (|- $e1 $e2))

;; --- Tension detector ---
;; Two statements about same term with opposing frequency
;; Returns tension magnitude as frequency gap
(= (tension? ((--> $s $p) (stv $f1 $c1)) ((--> $s $p) (stv $f2 $c2)))
   (let $gap (abs (- $f1 $f2))
     (if (> $gap 0.4) (tension $s $p $gap) (no-tension))))
"))))
