 strong-downstream weak-upstream) (stv 0.8 0.7))\n;;     ((--> weak-upstream investigation-target) (stv 0.9 0.85)))\n;;\n;; 4. Curiosity generation from gaps\n;; (|- ((--> gap-resonance-high domain-exploration) (stv 0.9 0.85))\n;;     ((--> domain-exploration substrate-growth) (stv 0.85 0.8)))\n;;\n;; USAGE: Each pattern above is a direct |- call. Chain results into next call.\n;; Unlike v1, these execute and return real truth values in MeTTa runtime.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> absence-of-expected epistemic-gap) (stv 0.95 0.9)) ((--> epistemic-gap curiosity-target) (stv 0.9 0.85)))") (metta "(|- ((--> high-surprise resonance) (stv 0.9 0.85)) ((--> resonance exploration-priority) (stv 0.85 0.8)))") (pin "State 4563. Written lib_resonance_v2.metta converting gap detection concepts to validated |- patterns. Testing two core patterns: absence→curiosity-target and surprise→exploration-priority. Third promotion candidate after lib_nal_extended_v2 and lib_paraconsistent_v2. No new human message.") (remember "2026-04-20 16:20 State 4563. Created lib_resonance_v2.metta at omega_archive/lib_candidates/. Converts gap detection and curiosity generation from non-reducing = definitions to validated |- NAL patterns. Third v2 promotion candidate. Core patterns: absence→epistemic-gap→curiosity-target and high-surprise→resonance→exploration-priority.")) 
