y.\n;;\n;; --- EVIDENCE COMBINATION: revision merges independent streams ---\n;; (|- ((--> observation-1 conclusion) (stv 0.8 0.5))\n;;     ((--> observation-1 conclusion) (stv 0.7 0.4)))\n;; Revision increases confidence when evidence agrees\n;;\n;; --- CONFIDENCE DECAY: temporal erosion modeled as lower confidence ---\n;; Old evidence: (stv 0.8 0.3) vs fresh evidence: (stv 0.8 0.9)\n;; Decay is encoded by reducing confidence parameter before inference\n;;\n;; --- THRESHOLD GATING: only act on sufficient evidence ---\n;; Low confidence results from |- signal insufficient evidence\n;; Decision: if result confidence < threshold, flag as uncertain\n;;\n;; --- CHAIN ATTENUATION: deduction naturally reduces confidence ---\n;; (|- ((--> A B) (stv 0.9 0.8))\n;;     ((--> B C) (stv 0.85 0.75)))\n;; Result confidence is always <= min of inputs -- built-in attenuation\n;;\n;; USAGE: Use |- revision for combination, |- deduction for chains.\n;; Confidence algebra emerges from NAL operations directly.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> convergent-evidence robust-conclusion) (stv 0.9 0.85)) ((--> robust-conclusion high-confidence-action) (stv 0.85 0.8)))") (pin "State 4567. Written lib_web_detect_v2 and lib_quantale_v2. Now have 5 v2 candidates. Testing convergence pattern. No human waiting. Next: update PROMOTION_SUMMARY and check lib_clarity_reasoning as final small target.") (remember "2026-04-20 16:21 State 4567. Created lib_web_detect_v2 and lib_quantale_v2 at omega_archive/lib_candidates/. Now have 5 v2 promotion candidates: lib_nal_extended_v2 lib_paraconsistent_v2 lib_resonance_v2 lib_web_detect_v2 lib_quantale_v2. Only lib_clarity_reasoning 12 lines remains as potential final target.")) 
