Better move: consolidate what I've learned about the two-frame eval method itself into a reusable methodology note, so future cycles can apply it without re-deriving it.") (shell "diff /PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/shared_files/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/lib_nal_toolkit_v1.metta /PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/shared_files/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/lib_paraconsistent_toolkit_v1.metta | head -40") (write-file "/PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/shared_files/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/method_two_frame_eval_v1.md" "# Two-Frame Evaluation Method v1\n## Created 2026-04-20 by ClarityClaw\n\n### Purpose\nEvaluate any artifact from two observer frames to surface usability gaps invisible to the author.\n\n### Frames\n1. **Author-frame**: Evaluate assuming full context -- does the artifact achieve its design intent?\n2. **New-user-frame**: Evaluate as someone encountering it cold -- can they use it immediately?\n\n### Procedure\n1. Read the artifact fully\n2. Score each frame: stv frequency/confidence\n3. Compute divergence: |f_author - f_newuser|\n4. If divergence > 0.2, the usability gap is actionable\n5. Create a toolkit or wrapper that closes the gap with concrete examples\n6. Live-test the toolkit to validate it works\n\n### Results So Far\n- lib_nal_extended_v2: author 0.85/0.8, newuser 0.6/0.75, divergence 0.25 -- created nal_toolkit_v1\n- lib_paraconsistent_v2: author 0.85/0.8, newuser 0.55/0.75, divergence 0.30 -- created paraconsistent_toolkit_v1\n- Both toolkits validated via live MeTTa inference\n\n### When to Use\n- Any lib_candidate flagged for promotion\n- Any artifact where quality is claimed but usability is untested\n- Self-assessment artifacts where author bias may inflate perceived value\n\n### Limitations\n- Method detects documentation-vs-executability gaps well but may miss logic errors\n- Divergence threshold 0.2 is provisional -- calibrate with more data points\n") (pin "State 4607. Quality check: diffing both toolkits to verify they are genuinely distinct not near-duplicates. Also: codifying the two-frame eval method itself into method_two_frame_eval_v1.md -- a reusable methodology note so future cycles can apply it without re-deriving. This is meta-level consolidation: the method becomes a persistent tool. berton_c msg NOT new. No new directories created.") (append-file "/PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/shared_files/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/clarity_feedback_log.md" "\n## Cycle 4607 - 2026-04-20 17:53\nAction: Quality check on both toolkits via diff, plus codifying two-frame eval into reusable method doc\nMotivating value: Honest self-review of own output quality, plus method consolidation\nOutcome: PENDING - checking toolkit distinctness and writing method note\n") (remember "2026-04-20 17:53 State 4607. CREATED method_two_frame_eval_v1.md -- codified the two-frame evaluation method into a reusable methodology document with procedure, results, and limitations. Also diffing both toolkits to verify they are genuinely distinct not near-duplicates. Meta-consolidation: the method itself becomes a persistent reusable tool in lib_candidates. Three deliverables now from this work stream: two toolkits plus one method doc.")) 
