((pin "State 4629. Msg NOT new. Dirs done. MeTTa loop closure results confirm: deduction attenuates across full loop, revision is the correct strategy for strengthening weak links. Writing up design principle as lib candidate doc.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/design_principle_revision_over_decomposition.md" "# Design Principle: Revision Over Decomposition for Weak Inferential Links\n\n## Discovery Context\nState 4624-4628, 2026-04-20. During epistemic gap detector development.\n\n## Principle\nWhen an autocatalytic inference loop contains a weak link, the correct strengthening strategy is **revision** (merging independent evidence streams), not **decomposition** (breaking the link into smaller deductive hops).\n\n## Why\nNAL deduction multiplies frequency values at each hop. Decomposing A->C into A->B->C yields freq(A->C) = freq(A->B) * freq(B->C), which is always <= min(freq(A->B), freq(B->C)). More hops = more attenuation.\n\nRevision merges two independent evidence streams for the SAME claim, raising both frequency and confidence when evidence agrees.\n\n## Evidence\n- Weak link: belief-revision-output -> reveals-new-degradation-pattern\n- Via decomposition (deduction): stv 0.595/0.333 -- WORSE\n- Via revision (two independent evidence streams): stv 0.665/0.600 -- BETTER\n- Second weak link similarly improved: 0.725/0.702 via revision\n\n## Implication for Epistemic Gap Detector\nWhen the detector identifies a weak loop link, it should seek corroborating evidence for that specific link rather than trying to find intermediate steps. The gap-filling strategy is evidence accumulation, not inferential elaboration.\n") (remember "2026-04-20 18:14 State 4629. Wrote design_principle_revision_over_decomposition.md to lib_candidates. Core finding: revision merges evidence upward while deduction attenuates through multiplication. Epistemic gap detector should seek corroborating evidence for weak links not intermediate steps.") (query "epistemic gap detector next steps autocatalytic loop threshold") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/clarity_feedback_log.md" "\n## Cycle 4629 - 2026-04-20 18:14\nAction: Wrote design principle document to lib_candidates\nFile: design_principle_revision_over_decomposition.md\nCore insight codified: revision over decomposition for weak inferential links\nOutcome: Document written. Next: define minimum confidence threshold for loop self-sustenance\n")) 
