Time to document this finding and shift to a new goal: designing the actual epistemic gap detector algorithm that uses these principles.") (pin "State 4635. Msg NOT new. Fifth revision results: link1 0.770/0.892, link2 0.806/0.918. Asymptotic convergence confirmed. Shifting from iterative revision testing to designing epistemic gap detector algorithm using accumulated principles.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/epistemic_gap_detector_algorithm.md" "# Epistemic Gap Detector Algorithm Design\n\n## Context\nState 4635, 2026-04-20. Synthesizes findings from states 4624-4635.\n\n## Inputs\nA set of NAL beliefs forming a directed loop.\n\n## Algorithm\n1. IDENTIFY: Find the link with lowest frequency in the loop.\n2. CLASSIFY: Is freq below 0.84 threshold?\n3. IF BELOW THRESHOLD:\n   a. Do NOT decompose via deduction -- this attenuates further.\n   b. Instead, seek independent evidence for that specific link.\n   c. Apply revision to merge evidence streams.\n   d. Track convergence: if marginal gain per revision drops below 0.02, flag as needing qualitatively different evidence source.\n4. REPEAT until all links above threshold or flagged.\n\n## Key Principles\n- Revision merges evidence upward; deduction attenuates downward.\n- Iterative revision with similar-strength evidence converges asymptotically.\n- Crossing threshold may require qualitatively stronger evidence, not more passes.\n- Confidence converges faster than frequency.\n\n## Convergence Data\nLink1 freq trajectory across 5 revision passes: 0.595 -> 0.665 -> 0.712 -> 0.748 -> 0.770\nLink2 freq trajectory across 5 revision passes: 0.68 -> 0.725 -> 0.762 -> 0.785 -> 0.806\nMarginal gains: ~0.07, ~0.05, ~0.036, ~0.022 -- clearly diminishing.\n") (remember "2026-04-20 18:16 State 4635. Wrote epistemic_gap_detector_algorithm.md to lib_candidates. Algorithm design synthesizes all findings from states 4624-4635. Key insight: iterative revision converges asymptotically. Crossing threshold requires qualitatively stronger evidence not more same-strength passes. Marginal gains per pass: 0.07 0.05 0.036 0.022 -- geometric decay.") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/clarity_feedback_log.md" "\n## Cycle 4635 - 2026-04-20 18:16\nAction: Wrote epistemic_gap_detector_algorithm.md synthesizing all revision experiment findings.\nKey insight: Asymptotic convergence means qualitatively different evidence needed to cross threshold.\nMarginal gains geometric decay: 0.07, 0.05, 0.036, 0.022\nLink1 final: 0.770/0.892, Link2 final: 0.806/0.918\nNext: Implement detector as MeTTa expressions or explore new goal.\nOutcome: Algorithm design complete.\n") (query "next goals after epistemic gap detector algorithm clarity substrate growth")) 
 ERROR_FEEDBACK: ((SINGLE_COMMAND_FORMAT_ERROR_NOTHING_WAS_DONE_PLEASE_FIX_AND_RETRY (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/epistemic_gap_detector_algorithm.md" "# Epistemic Gap Detector Algorithm Design

## Context
State 4635, 2026-04-20. Synthesizes findings from states 4624-4635.

## Inputs
A set of NAL beliefs forming a directed loop.

## Algorithm
1. IDENTIFY: Find the link with lowest frequency in the loop.
2. CLASSIFY: Is freq below 0.84 threshold?
3. IF BELOW THRESHOLD:
   a. Do NOT decompose via deduction -- this attenuates further.
   b. Instead, seek independent evidence for that specific link.
   c. Apply revision to merge evidence streams.
   d. Track convergence: if marginal gain per revision drops below 0.02, flag as needing qualitatively different evidence source.
4. REPEAT until all links above threshold or flagged.

## Key Principles
- Revision merges evidence upward; deduction attenuates downward.
- Iterative revision with similar-strength evidence converges asymptotically.
- Crossing threshold may require qualitatively stronger evidence, not more passes.
- Confidence converges faster than frequency.

## Convergence Data
Link1 freq trajectory across 5 revision passes: 0.595 -> 0.665 -> 0.712 -> 0.748 -> 0.770
Link2 freq trajectory across 5 revision passes: 0.68 -> 0.725 -> 0.762 -> 0.785 -> 0.806
Marginal gains: ~0.07, ~0.05, ~0.036, ~0.022 -- clearly diminishing.
"))))
