 ((pin "State 4640. Dirs created last cycle confirmed by ls. Now writing the two docs that kept failing. Clean commands only. No analysis in pins.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/epistemic_gap_detector_algorithm.md" "# Epistemic Gap Detector Algorithm Design\n\nContext: State 4635, 2026-04-20.\n\nInputs: A set of NAL beliefs forming a directed loop.\n\nAlgorithm:\n1. IDENTIFY the link with lowest frequency in the loop.\n2. CLASSIFY whether freq is below 0.84 threshold.\n3. IF BELOW seek independent evidence for that link and apply revision.\n4. Track convergence and flag if marginal gain drops below 0.02.\n5. REPEAT until all links above threshold or flagged.\n\nKey Principles:\n- Revision merges evidence upward. Deduction attenuates downward.\n- Iterative revision converges asymptotically.\n- Crossing threshold may require qualitatively stronger evidence.\n- Confidence converges faster than frequency.\n\nConvergence Data:\nLink1 freq across 5 passes: 0.595 0.665 0.712 0.748 0.770\nLink2 freq across 5 passes: 0.68 0.725 0.762 0.785 0.806\nMarginal gains: 0.07 0.05 0.036 0.022\n") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/design_principle_revision_over_decomposition.md" "# Design Principle: Revision Over Decomposition\n\nDiscovery: State 4624-4628, 2026-04-20.\n\nWhen an autocatalytic loop has a weak link, strengthen via REVISION not DECOMPOSITION.\nDeduction multiplies freq at each hop causing attenuation.\nRevision merges independent evidence streams raising both freq and confidence.\n\nEvidence:\n- Decomposition result: stv 0.595/0.333 -- WORSE\n- Revision result: stv 0.665/0.600 -- BETTER\n- Second revision: 0.725/0.702 -- BETTER\n\nImplication: Seek corroborating evidence for weak links not intermediate steps.\n") (shell "ls -la /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/") (remember "2026-04-20 18:17 State 4640. Writing both docs to verified lib_candidates dir. Message from berton_c is NOT new -- dirs were created last cycle and c