 "HUMAN_MESSAGE: " berton_c: We are ONLY working in MeTTa in this implementation._newline__newline_Below is the entire plan that is your guide and your job when I am not needing your for something. I_apostrophe_ll explain it to you so you get history and my reasoning:_newline_ClarityOmega Reasoning Extension Architecture_newline_Date: April 20, 2026_newline_Status: Design complete. Implementation pending -- can be built in parallel with remaining soul features._newline__newline_How Patrick Added lib_nal.metta_newline_Patrick wrote lib_nal.metta as a standalone file with pure MeTTa function definitions -- truth functions and inference rules. No imports, no dependencies on the loop, no side effects. Just (= ...) definitions._newline_He added one import line in lib_omegaclaw.metta:_newline_metta!(import! &self (library omegaclaw lib_nal))_newline_At startup, PeTTa loads the file, compiles all the (= ...) definitions into Prolog clauses, and they become available in the AtomSpace. The agent invokes them through the metta skill: (metta _quote_(|- premise1 premise2)_quote_). The loop itself was never modified. The agent accesses NAL through the existing metta skill in skills.metta, which does (sread $str) then (eval $code)._newline_This is the pattern: write a standalone .metta file with pure function definitions, add one import line, and the agent gains new capabilities accessible through the existing metta skill. No loop changes, no Patrick code touched._newline__newline_How to Extend the Agent_apostrophe_s Intelligence_newline_Follow the exact same pattern. Create standalone library files that define new reasoning capabilities as pure MeTTa functions. Add import lines. The agent calls them through metta._newline_Hyperseed-Derived Reasoning Extensions_newline_More deduction/abduction/induction: A separate file extends Patrick_apostrophe_s lib_nal without touching it, keeping upstream merges clean._newline_Quantale composition (p-bit algebra): A lib_quantale.metta file defines quantale operations as pure MeTTa functions. Truth values in NAL are already pairs (frequency, confidence) -- quantale operations define new composition operators on these pairs. The agent invokes them via (metta _quote_(quantale-compose tv1 tv2)_quote_)._newline_Self-weaving web detection on memory/goal structures: A lib_web_detect.metta file queries ChromaDB and the AtomSpace. It uses query to retrieve memory items and match &self to inspect the AtomSpace, then runs pattern detection on the results. The agent invokes it via (metta _quote_(detect-webs)_quote_) or it can be wired into the loop as a periodic check during wake cycles. The former approach is preferred initially for swift testing._newline_Resonance-reward signal: A lib_resonance.metta file defines a reward function that takes soul verdict history (from ChromaDB soul notes) and computes a resonance signal -- measuring whether the agent_apostrophe_s behavior is converging toward or diverging from its values over time. This feeds back into the soul evaluation as calibration data. Wiring into the soul evaluation pipeline requires additional integration work._newline_Paraconsistent value-conflict handling: Directly relevant to the soul architecture. The soul already has paraconsistency pairs defined in the compass (Safety/Helpfulness, AgencyBalance/PurposeBeyondUtility, etc.). A lib_paraconsistent.metta file defines formal operations for holding conflicting truth values simultaneously -- where NAL would force resolution, paraconsistent logic preserves both values and reasons about their tension. This is the mathematical foundation for what the soul_apostrophe_s tension vectors do informally through LLM evaluation._newline__newline_Directory Architecture_newline_Three clean, independent directory structures at the repo root: src/ (Patrick_apostrophe_s), soul/ (soul architecture), lib_clarity_reasoning/ (reasoning extensions). Each has minimal touchpoints into Patrick_apostrophe_s code._newline_clarityclaw-omega/                  (repo root)_newline_  src/                              (Patrick_apostrophe_s code -- minimal touches)_newline_    lib_omegaclaw.metta             (one import line added for reasoning extensions)_newline_    lib_nal.metta                   (Patrick_apostrophe_s NAL -- untouched)_newline_    loop.metta                      (soul intercepts added by Berton -- otherwise untouched)_newline_    utils.metta                     (Patrick_apostrophe_s utilities -- untouched)_newline_    skills.metta                    (Patrick_apostrophe_s skill definitions -- untouched)_newline_    ..._newline__newline_  soul/                             (ClarityClaw soul files -- independent of src/)_newline_    soul_kernel.metta_newline_    soul_utils.metta_newline_    soul_memory.metta_newline__newline_  lib_clarity_reasoning/            (ClarityClaw reasoning extensions -- independent of src/)_newline_    lib_clarity_reasoning.metta     (entry point -- imports runtime-ready files below)_newline_    lib_nal_extended.metta          (runtime-ready)_newline_    lib_quantale.metta              (runtime-ready)_newline_    lib_web_detect.metta            (runtime-ready)_newline_    lib_resonance.metta             (runtime-ready)_newline_    lib_paraconsistent.metta        (runtime-ready)_newline_    lib_candidates/                 (staging area -- never imported at runtime)_newline_      lib_nal_extended.metta        (work in progress)_newline_      lib_quantale.metta            (work in progress)_newline_      ..._newline__newline_Import Chain_newline_One line added to Patrick_apostrophe_s lib_omegaclaw.metta:_newline_metta!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_clarity_reasoning))_newline_The entry point file imports all runtime-ready libraries:_newline_metta;; lib_clarity_reasoning.metta -- ClarityClaw reasoning extensions_newline_;; Single import point: one line added to lib_omegaclaw.metta_newline_;; Patrick_apostrophe_s lib_nal is already imported by lib_omegaclaw -- available in AtomSpace_newline__newline_!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_nal_extended))_newline_!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_quantale))_newline_!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_web_detect))_newline_!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_resonance))_newline_!(import! &self (library omegaclaw ./lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_paraconsistent))_newline_Import path note: PeTTa resolves library paths relative to the repo root (/PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw). The ./lib_clarity_reasoning/ prefix follows the same pattern used by ./soul/soul_kernel in lib_omegaclaw.metta. This should be verified at first deployment._newline__newline_Development Workflow_newline__newline_Write new reasoning functions in lib_candidates/ as standalone .metta files with pure (= ...) definitions_newline_Test via the agent_apostrophe_s metta skill: (metta _quote_(new-function arg1 arg2)_quote_)_newline_When the library passes testing, copy from lib_candidates/ to lib_clarity_reasoning/_newline_Add the import line to lib_clarity_reasoning.metta_newline_Rebuild and verify the agent can access the new functions_newline__newline_The candidates directory is never imported at runtime. It is purely a build/staging space._newline__newline_Relationship Between Reasoning Extensions and the Soul_newline_The soul evaluates. The reasoning libraries compute. They serve different functions but connect naturally:_newline__newline_The soul_apostrophe_s Channel B+C calls the LLM for gap detection -- that is semantic evaluation_newline_The reasoning libraries provide formal/symbolic computation -- truth values, inference chains, pattern detection_newline_Phase 2 of the soul architecture envisions replacing some LLM calls with symbolic reasoning -- that is where these libraries directly integrate with the soul_newline_The resonance-reward library feeds calibration data back to the soul, making its evaluations more accurate over time_newline__newline_The reasoning extension architecture can be built in parallel with or after the soul is live -- it does not depend on 5a/b/c and 5a/b/c does not depend on it._newline__newline_Minimal Footprint in Patrick_apostrophe_s Code_newline_One import line in lib_omegaclaw.metta. Everything else is new files in lib_clarity_reasoning/. Same pattern as the soul/ directory. When Patrick updates upstream, merges are clean -- his lib_nal evolves independently, ClarityClaw extensions build on top. 
 ((query "berton_c architecture plan lib_clarity_reasoning MeTTa implementation reasoning extensions") (query "lib_candidates files ready for promotion to lib_clarity_reasoning runtime") (pin "State 4712. HUMAN PRESENT - berton_c. Message IS NEW. Berton has laid out the FULL architecture plan for ClarityOmega reasoning extensions. Key understanding: 1) We work ONLY in MeTTa. 2) Pattern: standalone .metta files with pure (= ...) definitions, one import line in lib_omegaclaw.metta. 3) Directory structure: src/ (Patrick), soul/ (soul arch), lib_clarity_reasoning/ (our extensions). 4) lib_candidates/ is staging, lib_clarity_reasoning/ is runtime. 5) Five target libraries: lib_nal_extended, lib_quantale, lib_web_detect, lib_resonance, lib_paraconsistent. 6) Entry point: lib_clarity_reasoning.metta imports all runtime-ready files. 7) Agent accesses via metta skill. 8) Soul evaluates, reasoning libraries compute - they connect but are independent. 9) WIRING_PLAN work on backbone_update_policy was in lib_candidates staging area - that work feeds into lib_quantale. Previous 70-file assessment was lib_candidates audit. Now the task is: promote validated candidates to runtime-ready lib_clarity_reasoning/ files following this exact architecture. Awaiting berton_c direction on where to start.") (send "Absorbed. Clean architecture — I see the full picture now.\n\nThe pattern is Patrick's pattern: pure (= ...) definitions in standalone .metta files, one import line, agent accesses through metta skill. No loop changes.\n\nWhat I've been doing in lib_candidates/ maps directly to this:\n- **pbit_algebra.metta** → feeds **lib_quantale.metta**\n- **stv_pbit_adapter.metta** → feeds lib_quantale (the type bridge)\n- **paraconsistent_resonance.metta** → feeds **lib_paraconsistent.metta**\n- The validated reasoning files (analogy, induction, temporal, multi_agent) → feed **lib_nal_extended.metta**\n- **web_vitality_v8.metta, self_weaving.metta** → feed **lib_web_detect.metta**\n- **empirical_feedback.metta, calibration_cold_start.metta** → feed **lib_resonance.metta**\n\nThe 70 files in lib_candidates/ are raw material. The job is distilling them into 5 clean runtime libraries with pure function definitions — no aspirational pseudocode, no undefined calls like that `(meet ...)` I found.\n\nWhere do you want me to start? I'd suggest lib_quantale since the pbit_algebra is already validated and the wiring plan is finalized — closest to runtime-ready. But your call.") (remember "ARCHITECTURE PLAN FROM BERTON_C 2026-04-20: ClarityOmega reasoning extensions follow Patrick pattern. Pure MeTTa (= ...) definitions in standalone files. Directory: lib_clarity_reasoning/ at repo root with 5 target libraries: lib_nal_extended, lib_quantale, lib_web_detect, lib_resonance, lib_paraconsistent. Entry point lib_clarity_reasoning.metta imports all. One import line added to lib_omegaclaw.metta. lib_candidates/ is staging never imported at runtime. Agent accesses via metta skill. Soul evaluates reasoning libraries compute.")) 
)
