((shell "ls -la /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/ 2>/dev/null") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_quantale.metta" ";; lib_quantale.metta -- ClarityClaw Reasoning Extensions\n;; Quantale composition (p-bit algebra) for paraconsistent truth values\n;; Pattern: pure (= ...) definitions, no imports, no side effects\n;; A p-bit is a paraconsistent truth value: (mk-pbit strength confidence)\n;; Extends NAL stv pairs with quantale composition operators\n;; Agent invokes via: (metta \"(q-mul (mk-pbit 0.8 0.9) (mk-pbit 0.7 0.85))\")\n\n;; === Core Type ===\n(: pbit Type)\n(: mk-pbit (-> Number Number pbit))\n\n;; === Quantale Multiplication (sequential composition) ===\n;; strength multiplies, confidence takes minimum\n(: q-mul (-> pbit pbit pbit))\n(= (q-mul (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2))\n   (mk-pbit (* $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n;; === Quantale Join (parallel composition / disjunction) ===\n(: q-join (-> pbit pbit pbit))\n(= (q-join (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2))\n   (mk-pbit (max $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n;; === Quantale Meet (conjunction) ===\n(: q-meet (-> pbit pbit pbit))\n(= (q-meet (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2))\n   (mk-pbit (min $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n;; === Negation (paraconsistent - flips strength, preserves confidence) ===\n(: q-neg (-> pbit pbit))\n(= (q-neg (mk-pbit $s $c))\n   (mk-pbit (- 1.0 $s) $c))\n\n;; === Bridge: stv to pbit ===\n(: stv-to-pbit (-> Atom pbit))\n(= (stv-to-pbit (stv $s $c)) (mk-pbit $s $c))\n\n;; === Bridge: pbit to stv ===\n(: pbit-to-stv (-> pbit Atom))\n(= (pbit-to-stv (mk-pbit $s $c)) (stv $s $c))\n\n;; === Governance bridge: takes two stv, returns q-meet as pbit ===\n(: governance-pbit (-> Atom Atom pbit))\n(= (governance-pbit (stv $s1 $c1) (stv $s2 $c2))\n   (q-meet (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2)))\n\n;; === Unit elements ===\n(: q-top pbit)\n(= q-top (mk-pbit 1.0 1.0))\n(: q-bot pbit)\n(= q-bot (mk-pbit 0.0 1.0))\n(: q-unknown pbit)\n(= q-unknown (mk-pbit 0.5 0.0))\n") (shell "cat /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/analogy_reasoning_v1.metta 2>/dev/null | head -40") (shell "cat /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/analogy_validated.metta 2>/dev/null | head -40") (pin "State 4716. Msg NOT new. Self-directed build. WROTE lib_quantale.metta as first runtime-ready library in lib_clarity_reasoning/. Contains: q-mul, q-join, q-meet, q-neg, stv-to-pbit, pbit-to-stv, governance-pbit bridge, unit elements. Pure (= ...) definitions, no imports, no side effects. Now reading analogy candidates to begin assembling lib_nal_extended.metta. Target: all 5 runtime libraries built.")) 
