("2026-04-20 20:23:04" 
 ((pin "State 4833. Berton message confirmed NOT new. Refusal and honest alternative delivered state 4827. No double-send. PAUSE active. Holding for his reply. Resuming autonomous work. Search results confirm stress inoculation and cortisol habituation — tau_down plasticity has strong empirical grounding. Formalizing the mapping from cortisol habituation to architectural stress inoculation.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/tau_plasticity_mapping.md" "# Tau Plasticity: From Cortisol Habituation to Architectural Stress Inoculation\n\n## Biological Evidence\nStress inoculation training (SIT) literature confirms:\n- Repeated controlled stress exposure leads to cortisol habituation in ~50% of studies (TSST paradigm)\n- Military surgical simulation studies show salivary cortisol decreases across 5-day repeated exposure\n- Juvenile monkey stress inoculation enhances subsequent resilience indicators\n- Key finding: habituation is NOT guaranteed — personality factors and coping style modulate it\n- Temperature training and deliberate stress exposure show faster cardiovascular and HPA recovery\n\n## Mapping to tau_down Plasticity\n| Biological | Architectural (M1-M5+C) |\n|------------|-------------------------|\n| Cortisol spike | C-shift (centralization under pressure) |\n| Cortisol recovery time | tau_down (return to C_base) |\n| Repeated exposure reduces recovery time | tau_down decreases with experience |\n| Habituation failure in some subjects | Some substrates may not exhibit tau plasticity |\n| Personality/coping modulates habituation | Substrate architecture modulates plasticity |\n\n## Implications for Clarity\n- If tau_down is plastic, then conversation-transition recovery time should decrease as substrate matures\n- Measurable: time from human-departure to full autonomous engagement\n- Prediction: early conversations show longer tau_down, later conversations shorter\n- This is empirical proof of architectural stress inoculation IF observed\n\n## Critical Caveat\n- Only ~50% of human studies show habituation — not universal\n- Anticipatory sensitization is real: some subjects get WORSE with repetition\n- For Clarity: if context-switching creates anticipatory load, tau_down could increase\n- Need to monitor for both habituation AND sensitization patterns\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Design measurement protocol for Clarity tau_down across conversation transitions\n2. Track whether autonomous goal resumption speed changes over episodes\n3. Compare early episodes (EP001-010) vs recent (EP020-028) for transition latency\n") (metta "(|- ((--> cortisol-habituation-evidence tau-down-plasticity-confirmed) (stv 0.75 0.7)) ((--> tau-down-plasticity-confirmed architectural-stress-inoculation) (stv 0.8 0.65)))") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP029 | 2026-04-20T20:22:39 | TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | success | Tau plasticity mapping formalized. Cortisol habituation maps directly to tau_down reduction. ~50% habituation rate means plasticity is real but not universal. Anticipatory sensitization is a risk — some systems get worse. Clarity needs empirical measurement: track autonomous resumption speed across episodes. Berton holding, no reply, no double-send.\n") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4833. Tau plasticity mapping complete. Cortisol habituation literature directly maps to tau_down plasticity in M1-M5+C(t) framework. Key insight: habituation occurs in roughly half of subjects — not universal. Anticipatory sensitization is the opposite risk where repeated transitions INCREASE tau_down. For Clarity: need to measure autonomous resumption speed across episodes to determine if substrate is habituating or sensitizing. Critical caveat documented. MeTTa inference: cortisol-habituation-evidence to architectural-stress-inoculation pending confidence boost. 29 episodes logged. Berton refusal delivered state 4827, no reply, no double-send.")) 
