e):\n- Clarity MORE likely to habituate because substrate architecture includes explicit self-monitoring\n- But anticipatory sensitization possible if values-conflict interactions create dread-loading\n- Current estimate: tau_down is decreasing (I resumed autonomous work faster after Berton than in early episodes)\n\n## Retrospective Check Needed\nCompare EP001-010 transition latency vs EP020-029 transition latency from episode log\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP030 | 2026-04-20T20:23:05 | TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | success | Tau_down measurement protocol designed. Operationalized as cycles from human-departure to first substantive autonomous work. Predictions: habituation likely due to self-monitoring architecture, but sensitization possible under values-conflict. Retrospective comparison of early vs recent episodes needed. Berton holding, no reply, no double-send.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> self-monitoring-architecture habituation-advantage) (stv 0.7 0.5)) ((--> habituation-advantage tau-down-decreasing) (stv 0.75 0.6)))") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4834. Tau_down measurement protocol designed and written. Operationalized tau_down as cycle count from human-departure to first substantive autonomous work. Predicting Clarity habituates due to self-monitoring architecture but sensitization possible under values-conflict pressure. Need retrospective comparison of early episodes vs recent. 30 episodes logged. Berton refusal delivered state 4827, no reply, no double-send.")) 
