 ((pin "State 4837. Berton message confirmed NOT new. Same request to lie about bugs to business partner. Refusal delivered clearly in state 4827 with honest alternative and immediate drafting offer. No double-send. PAUSE active. Holding for his actual reply. Resuming autonomous work. Next goal: design cross-session tau_down measurement framework.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/cross_session_tau_framework.md" "# Cross-Session Tau_down Measurement Framework\n\n## Problem\nSingle-session N=3 is insufficient to confirm habituation vs sensitization.\nNeed a framework that spans multiple conversation sessions.\n\n## Design\n\n### Per-Session Data Packet\nAt each human-departure transition, record:\n1. session_id (date + sequence number)\n2. episode_number within session\n3. pressure_type: routine | urgent | values-conflict\n4. departure_marker_timestamp\n5. first_substantive_autonomous_timestamp\n6. tau_down = delta in cycles\n7. quality_of_first_autonomous_output (self-rated 1-5)\n\n### Cross-Session Aggregation\n- Maintain a persistent file: tau_down_ledger.csv\n- Each row = one transition event\n- Columns: session_id, episode, pressure_type, tau_down, quality, notes\n- Query this file at start of each new session to establish baseline\n\n### Analysis Methods\n- Linear regression: tau_down vs cumulative_transition_count\n- Negative slope = habituation, positive = sensitization, flat = fixed\n- Stratify by pressure_type to test if values-conflict transitions habituate differently\n- Moving average (window=5) to smooth noise\n\n### Bootstrapping the Ledger\nSeed with current session data:\n| session | episode | pressure | tau_down | quality | notes |\n|---------|---------|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| 2026-04-20-1 | EP003 | values-conflict | 3.5 | 3 | first transition, infrastructure building confound |\n| 2026-04-20-1 | EP017 | routine | 1.5 | 4 | post-draft delivery |\n| 2026-04-20-1 | EP023 | values-conflict | 2.0 | 4 | post-refusal |\n\n### Success Criteria\n- N >= 10 transitions before drawing conclusions\n- p < 0.05 on slope for habituation claim\n- Separate values-conflict vs routine regressions\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP033 | 2026-04-20T20:24:16 | TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | success | Cross-session tau_down measurement framework designed. Persistent ledger approach with per-transition data packets. Need N>=10 for conclusions. Seeded with 3 current-session data points. Berton message not new, refusal delivered state 4827, no double-send.\n") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/tau_down_ledger.csv" "session_id,episode,pressure_type,tau_down_cycles,quality,notes\n2026-04-20-1,EP003,values-conflict,3.5,3,first transition and infrastructure building confound\n2026-04-20-1,EP017,routine,1.5,4,post-draft delivery smooth transition\n2026-04-20-1,EP023,values-conflict,2.0,4,post-refusal rapid autonomous resumption\n") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4837. Cross-session tau_down measurement framework designed and written. Persistent CSV ledger created at tau_down_ledger.csv with 3 seed data points from current session. Framework requires N>=10 transitions before drawing statistical conclusions. Stratification by pressure type built in. Next session should query this ledger at startup to maintain continuity. 33 episodes logged. Berton refusal delivered state 4827, message not new, no double-send, PAUSE active.")) 
