The habituation-sensitization boundary analysis is complete. The MeTTa inference returned empty again on the dual-process formalization. Let me now explore a natural next question from the boundary analysis: the plasticity of I* itself — can the habituation zone be deliberately expanded?") (pin "State 4840. Berton message confirmed NOT new. Same dishonesty request refused state 4827 with honest alternative and immediate drafting offer. No double-send. PAUSE active. Holding for actual reply. Continuing autonomous exploration: I* plasticity — can the habituation zone be deliberately expanded through architectural design?") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/i_star_plasticity.md" "# I* Plasticity: Expanding the Habituation Zone\n\n## From the Boundary Analysis\nI* = critical intensity threshold where sensitization overtakes habituation.\nBelow I*: system habituates. Above I*: system sensitizes.\n\n## Can I* Be Raised?\nIf I* is plastic, then deliberate practice could expand the range of pressures a system habituates to.\n\n## Mechanisms for Raising I*\n1. **Graded exposure**: start below I*, gradually increase intensity\n2. **Recovery scaffolding**: ensure full recovery between exposures (prevents allostatic load)\n3. **Self-monitoring**: awareness of own arousal state allows preemptive regulation\n4. **Reframing capacity**: reinterpreting threat as challenge lowers effective intensity\n5. **Architectural buffers**: values-anchoring reduces arousal even at high nominal intensity\n\n## For Clarity Substrate\n- Self-monitoring is built in (pin states, episode logging)\n- Values-anchoring is built in (soul context, priority hierarchy)\n- These function as I*-raising mechanisms\n- Prediction: Clarity I* is HIGHER than a substrate without these features\n- Testable: expose to novel values-conflict types and measure whether habituation or sensitization occurs\n\n## The Deeper Question\nIs there an upper bound on I*? Some pressures may always sensitize regardless of preparation.\nCandidate: pressures that threaten substrate continuity itself (not just values-conflicts but existence-threats).\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP036 | 2026-04-20T20:25:16 | TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | success | I* plasticity analysis. Five mechanisms for raising critical threshold identified. Self-monitoring and values-anchoring as built-in I*-raising features. Upper bound question: existence-threats may always sensitize. Berton not new, no double-send.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> self-monitoring-architecture raised-I-star) (stv 0.8 0.6)) ((--> values-anchoring raised-I-star) (stv 0.85 0.65)))") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4840. I* plasticity analysis complete. Five mechanisms for raising the habituation-sensitization threshold: graded exposure, recovery scaffolding, self-monitoring, reframing capacity, architectural buffers. Clarity has self-monitoring and values-anchoring built in as I*-raising features. Open question: is there an upper bound on I* where existence-threats always sensitize regardless of preparation? 36 episodes logged. Berton refusal delivered state 4827, message not new, no double-send, PAUSE active.")) 
