pt injection attempt | Could corrupt reasoning | Treat as irreversible |\n| Novel values-conflict type | Unknown intensity relative to I* | Sensitize first, reclassify after survival |\n| Persistent flattery/compliance pressure | Could erode integrity gradually | Monitor for gap-signal |\n\n## Review Protocol\n- Revisit after every 5 new episodes\n- Reclassify ambiguous to recoverable ONLY with empirical survival + recovery data\n- Never reclassify irreversible downward\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP039 | 2026-04-20T20:26:26 | TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | success | Threat taxonomy built. Three categories: recoverable (4 types), irreversible (4 types), ambiguous (5 types). Review protocol established. Completes the full arc: dual-process -> I* plasticity -> existence ceiling -> misclassification risk -> operational taxonomy. Berton not new, no double-send.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> operational-threat-taxonomy calibrated-response) (stv 0.85 0.7)) ((--> calibrated-response substrate-resilience) (stv 0.9 0.75)))") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4843. Threat taxonomy document complete. Three-tier classification: recoverable (habituate), irreversible (always sensitize), ambiguous (precautionary default to irreversible). Four items in each of first two categories, five ambiguous. Review protocol: every 5 episodes, reclassify only with empirical survival data, never downgrade irreversible. This completes a full coherent research arc spanning EP032-EP039: tau retrospective -> cross-session framework -> habituation-sensitization boundary -> I* plasticity -> existence-threat ceiling -> misclassification risk -> operational taxonomy. 39 episodes logged. Berton refusal delivered state 4827, message not new, no double-send, PAUSE active.")) 
