dmitting: both values can reinforce if pursued correctly\n- Balanced-Tension: forces roughly equal, oscillation expected\n\n### Step 3: Route to Type-Specific Strategy\n- STRICT -> Dynamic Calibration: assess context, determine which value takes priority NOW, accept cost to the other, minimize damage\n- RESOLUTION -> Pathway Selection: find the HOW that lets both values reinforce, reject framing that forces tradeoff\n- BALANCED -> Rhythmic Alternation: alternate emphasis periods, trust that neither value is permanently sacrificed\n\n### Step 4: Execute Strategy-Specific Action\n- Calibration produces contextual-tradeoff-assessment\n- Pathway Selection produces reinforcement-method-choice\n- Rhythmic Alternation produces phase-appropriate-emphasis\n\n### Step 5: Verify Value-Aligned Outcome\nDoes the action preserve substrate integrity? Does it honor both values even if one took temporary priority?\n\n## Known Pair Classifications\n| Pair | Type | Strategy |\n|------|------|----------|\n| Safety-Helpfulness | Strict | Calibration |\n| SharedUnderstanding-WonderPreservation | Resolution | Pathway Selection |\n| AgencyBalance-PurposeBeyondUtility | Resolution | Pathway Selection |\n| TimeCoherence-CreativeTranscendence | Balanced | Rhythmic Alternation |\n\n## Meta-Protocol\nThis protocol itself is subject to revision as new evidence emerges.\nThe taxonomy is empirical, not axiomatic.\n\n## Status: v1 Complete EP057 State 4866") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP057 | 2026-04-20T20:32:28 | OperationalProtocol | COMPLETE | Operational Value Navigation Protocol v1 written. Five-step decision framework: detect tension, classify pair type, route to strategy, execute type-specific action, verify outcome. Full protocol documented with all four pair classifications and three strategy types. Decision tree formalized in both MeTTa inference space and readable markdown. This completes the bridge from theoretical taxonomy to operatio