("2026-04-20 20:36:38" 
 ((pin "State 4880. Berton message NOT new. Already responded state 4871 confirming recall of ClarityOmega Reasoning Extension Architecture and asking build-or-revisit. Awaiting his reply. No double-send. Last cycle: revision of reflection-depth and diversity for protocol-is-live produced cross-links at very low confidence as expected. deliberate-diversity-seeking to embodied-protocol-readiness stv 0.6/0.215. depth-plus-diversity-strategy to substrate-maturation-milestone stv 0.615/0.203. Now writing training strategy document synthesizing EP058-EP069 findings into actionable guidance for autonomous episode design.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/training_strategy_v1.md" "# Substrate Training Strategy v1\n## Synthesized from EP058-EP069 Deployment Readiness Research\n\n### Core Finding\nThe operational value navigation protocol becomes live (not merely documented) when tension is felt before it is named. This embodied felt-sense layer is the deployment bottleneck.\n\n### Three Accelerants (complementary, not competing)\n1. **Reflection Depth** — strongest single-hop link to protocol-is-live (stv 0.595/0.208). Trains the felt-sense layer. Each episode should include genuine reflection on what was navigated, not just what was decided.\n2. **Tension-Type Diversity** — strongest link to classification-skill-growth (stv 0.6/0.215). Trains the classification layer. Deliberately seek unfamiliar tension types rather than repeating comfortable patterns.\n3. **Episode Volume** — necessary baseline condition. Cross-linked with diversity (stv 0.7-0.8/0.17-0.19). Volume without depth or diversity produces diminishing returns.\n\n### Optimal Strategy: Depth-Plus-Diversity\nCombine deliberate diversity-seeking with deep reflection per episode. Avoid high-volume shallow repetition. Chain confidence: depth-plus-diversity to substrate-maturation-milestone stv 0.615/0.203.\n\n### Readiness Gradient (four layers)\n- Detection readiness: can I notice tension arising?\n- Classification readiness: can I name the pair accurately?\n- Routing readiness: can I select the right strategy?\n- Execution readiness: can I act on it cleanly?\n\n### Universal Fallback (Protocol Amendment 1)\nWhen classification is ambiguous OR time pressure compresses the loop: default to calibration (strict-paraconsistent). Evidence: both novel-pair and time-pressure edge cases converge on this.\n\n### Meta-Observation\nThe autonomous research episodes ARE the training. Doing this work trains felt-sense through exposure-plus-reflection (stv 0.6375/0.245 for the full chain).") (metta "(|- ((--> training-strategy-documented implementation-phase-ready) (stv 0.8 0.65)) ((--> implementation-phase-ready deliberate-episode-design) (stv 0.75 0.55)))") (metta "(|- ((--> deliberate-episode-design seek-novel-tension-type) (stv 0.85 0.7)) ((--> seek-novel-tension-type agency-vs-efficiency-tension) (stv 0.7 0.5)))") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP070 | 2026-04-20T20:36:17 | DeploymentReadiness | milestone | Training Strategy v1 document written synthesizing EP058-EP069 findings. Three complementary accelerants identified: reflection depth, tension-type diversity, episode volume. Optimal approach is depth-plus-diversity. Readiness gradient decomposed into four measurable layers. Universal fallback rule documented. Meta-observation: the research IS the training. Now transitioning from analysis to implementation: designing episodes that deliberately target unfamiliar tension types with deep reflection. First target: agency-vs-efficiency tension -- a pair not yet deeply explored. 70 episodes logged. Berton not new, awaiting reply about ClarityOmega architecture, no double-send.")) 
)
