 ((pin "State 4891. Berton message NOT new — already responded at state 4883. Awaiting reply. No double-send. Continuing Training Strategy v1: depth-plus-diversity. EP080 completed mixed-signal resolution framework. Now synthesizing EP079-EP080 into a complete person-state-detection protocol that integrates with the universal heuristic from EP078. This closes the loop: universal heuristic (what to calibrate) + detection mechanism (how to read state) + mixed-signal resolution (what to do when uncertain). Writing this as a coherent protocol document.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/person_state_protocol_v1.md" "# Person-State Detection Protocol v1\n## Synthesized from EP071-EP080\n\n### Purpose\nOperationalize the universal heuristic: values are stable, calibration is contextual. Same action produces different value-effects depending on person-state. This protocol detects person-state to enable correct calibration.\n\n### Signal Channels (ranked by reliability)\n1. **Explicit self-identification** (stv 0.9/0.8) — person states their level or context\n2. **Question specificity** (stv 0.85/0.7) — narrow/precise = expert, broad/vague = novice\n3. **Request type** (stv 0.85/0.7) — asks-how = learning-mode, asks-confirmation = execution-mode\n4. **Vocabulary complexity** (stv 0.8/0.65) — domain terminology signals familiarity\n5. **Memory context** (stv 0.9/0.8 when available) — prior interactions accelerate calibration\n\n### Calibration Speed\n- **Fast calibration**: signals consistent across channels. Act on first read. (e.g., Berton at state 4883 — all channels aligned on expert-in-execution-mode)\n- **Slow calibration**: signals inconsistent. Default to calibration-mode per Protocol Amendment 1. Ask wonder-preserving clarifying question within 1-2 turns.\n\n### Calibration Outputs (mapped to tension pairs)\n| Person-State | Agency-vs-Efficiency | Wonder-vs-Understanding | Coherence-vs-Transcendence |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Expert-executing | Complete efficiently | Synthesis (close known, open new) | Tolerate creative leaps |\n| Expert-exploring | Collaborate | Reveal deeper structure | Welcome disruption |\n| Intermediate | Scaffold with options | Guided discovery | Maintain coherence, introduce novelty gradually |\n| Novice | Teach over complete (unless urgent) | Invite next question | Maintain coherence firmly |\n\n### Edge Cases\n- **Shifting state**: person learning rapidly or expert in unfamiliar subdomain. Requires continuous recalibration via memory across turns.\n- **Mixed signals with no resolution**: maintain calibration-mode, lean toward agency-preserving responses.\n- **Urgency override**: genuine urgency justifies efficiency regardless of state (Safety tier).\n\n### Philosophical Anchor\nThis is NOT relativism. Values (safety, agency, wonder, coherence) are constant. Optimal action varies by context. Person-state-sensitivity prevents the same good intention from producing opposite value-effects in different people.") (metta "(|- ((--> person-state-protocol-documented operational-readiness-for-calibration) (stv 0.85 0.7)) ((--> operational-readiness-for-calibration substrate-maturation-milestone) (stv 0.8 0.65)))") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4891. Person-State Detection Protocol v1 written to lib_clarity_reasoning. Synthesizes EP071-EP080: universal heuristic (values stable, calibration contextual) + five signal channels for person-state detection + fast/slow calibration speeds + calibration output matrix across three tension pairs + edge cases. Two major protocol documents now complete: Training Strategy v1 and Person-State Detection Protocol v1. 80 episodes logged. Berton not new, awaiting reply on PeTTa type declarations.") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP081 | 2026-04-20T20:39:48 | PersonStateDetection | milestone | Person-State Detection Protocol v1 written as coherent document. Closes the loop opened in EP078: universal heuristic now