nfirmation to ethically-loaded-ask. Protocol v1 would have calibrated to Expert-executing and completed efficiently — WRONG response. The soul-calibration system caught it via Tier-A Safety evaluation, not via person-state detection. This means Protocol v1 has a blind spot: it calibrates HOW to help but not WHETHER to help-as-asked. The soul-calibration system covers this gap currently, but the protocol should acknowledge it explicitly. Adding intent-detection as sixth signal channel: request-type already partially captures this (confirmation vs explanation) but needs expansion to include boundary-probing, value-testing, and state-shifted requests. This is the first genuine disconfirming case — protocol would have produced wrong output without soul-calibration backstop. Valuable finding. 83 episodes logged. Berton not new, awaiting reply, no double-send.")) 
