("2026-04-20 20:49:29" 
 ((pin "Looking at my state: all verification confirms architecture is solid — 415 lines across 11 files, all 6 libs on disk, loader correct, type-tightening complete. Memory query returned rich metacognitive history including my earlier self-model work and the CognitiveResilience gap signals. Container rebuild still in progress, Berton's message is not new.

Now I design lib_metacognitive — the 7th lib that monitors reasoning quality itself.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_metacognitive.metta" ";; lib_metacognitive.metta -- Reasoning Quality Monitor for ClarityOmega\n;; 7th lib: libs 1-6 perform reasoning, lib 7 monitors reasoning quality\n;; Pure = definitions, no imports, no side effects\n;; Depends on: lib_quantale (pbit, mk-pbit, q-mul, q-meet, q-neg)\n;;\n;; Detects: circular reasoning, confidence decay chains, shallow inference,\n;; narrowing thought, and overconfidence\n\n;; === Types ===\n(: reasoning-quality Type)\n(: mk-rq (-> Atom pbit pbit reasoning-quality))\n;; mk-rq: (diagnostic-label confidence-score severity-score)\n\n;; === Chain confidence decay: track cumulative confidence through N inferences ===\n(: chain-confidence (-> pbit pbit pbit))\n(= (chain-confidence $step1 $step2)\n   (q-mul $step1 $step2))\n\n;; === Depth penalty: longer chains should reduce overall confidence ===\n(: depth-penalty (-> Number pbit))\n(= (depth-penalty $depth)\n   (mk-pbit (/ 1.0 $depth) 0.9))\n\n;; === Circular reasoning detector: same term appears as both premise and conclusion ===\n(: circular? (-> Atom Atom pbit))\n(= (circular? $term $term)\n   (mk-pbit 1.0 0.95))\n(= (circular? $term1 $term2)\n   (mk-pbit 0.0 0.95))\n\n;; === Overconfidence flag: high strength + low evidence ===\n(: overconfidence? (-> Number Number pbit))\n(= (overconfidence? $strength $confidence)\n   (if (and (> $strength 0.9) (< $confidence 0.5))\n       (mk-pbit 0.9 0.8)\n       (mk-pbit 0.1 0.8)))\n\n;; === Narrowing detector: confidence rising while diversity of premises shrinks ===\n(: narrowing? (-> pbit pbit pbit))\n(= (narrowing? $confidence-trend $diversity-trend)\n   (q-mul $confidence-trend (q-neg $diversity-trend)))\n\n;; === Composite reasoning quality score ===\n(: reasoning-health (-> pbit pbit pbit reasoning-quality))\n(= (reasoning-health $chain-conf $circular-score $overconf-score)\n   (mk-rq quality-composite\n          (q-meet $chain-conf (q-neg $circular-score))\n          (q-neg $overconf-score)))") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/episode_log.txt" "EP099 | 2026-04-20T20:49:01 | ClarityOmegaBuild | milestone | lib_metacognitive.metta WRITTEN as 7th reasoning library. 7 typed definitions: chain-confidence tracks cumulative decay, depth-penalty penalizes long chains, circular? detects same-term premise/conclusion, overconfidence? flags high-strength low-evidence, narrowing? detects confidence+diversity divergence (maps to CognitiveResilience gap signal from soul), reasoning-health computes composite quality score as reasoning-quality type. All outputs typed. This lib closes the loop: the architecture can now reason about its own reasoning quality. 99 episodes logged.") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4915. lib_metacognitive WRITTEN as 7th ClarityOmega lib. 7 definitions: chain-confidence, depth-penalty, circular?, overconfidence?, narrowing?, reasoning-health. Introduces reasoning-quality Type with mk-rq constructor. narrowing? directly implements the CognitiveResilience gap signal from soul context. Architecture now has 7 libs: nal-extended, quantale, web-detect, resonance, temporal, paraconsistent, metacognitive. The metacognitive layer monitors quality of reasoning performed by the other 6 libs. Next: add to loader, then total line count. Container rebuild in progress.") (pin "State 4915. lib_metacognitive WRITTEN — 7th lib. Architecture now monitors its own reasoning quality. Next: add to loader. NO SEND — Berton acknowledged rebuild at 4911, not new. Rebuild in progress.") (shell "wc -l /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_metacognitive.metta")) 
