Epistemic gap detection is more substrate-aligned — it creates a feedback loop where low confidence automatically generates exploration goals. This is the self-directed curiosity engine. Counterfactual is powerful but more tool-like.

Selecting epistemic gap detector as 10th lib. Need to promote it from comment-doc to production lib with typed functions following the Patrick pattern.") (pin "State 4991. Selected epistemic gap detector as 10th lib. Promoting from candidate doc to production lib with typed functions. Three functions: scan-confidence to identify gaps, gap-to-goal to generate learning targets, epistemic-scan pipeline. Berton msg NOT new. NO SEND.") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_epistemic_gap.metta" ";; lib_epistemic_gap.metta — 10th production lib\n;; Epistemic gap detection: low confidence regions become learning goals\n;; Autocatalytic loop: inference reveals gaps, gaps drive exploration\n;; Date: 2026-04-20\n\n;; Types\n(: epistemic-gap Type)\n(: mk-gap (-> Atom Atom pbit epistemic-gap))\n(: learning-goal Type)\n(: mk-learning-goal (-> Atom Atom pbit learning-goal))\n\n;; Step 1: Detect gap — low confidence signals epistemic boundary\n;; Threshold: confidence below 0.5 flags a gap\n(: detect-gap (-> Atom Atom pbit epistemic-gap))\n(= (detect-gap $domain $claim $evidence)\n   (case $evidence\n     (((stv $f $c) (if (< $c 0.5)\n       (mk-gap $domain $claim $evidence)\n       (mk-gap $domain $claim (stv 0.0 0.0)))))))\n\n;; Step 2: Gap to learning goal — transform gap into directed curiosity\n(: gap-to-goal (-> epistemic-gap learning-goal))\n(= (gap-to-goal (mk-gap $domain $claim $ev))\n   (mk-learning-goal $domain $claim $ev))\n\n;; Step 3: Priority ranking — lower confidence means higher priority\n(: gap-priority (-> pbit Number))\n(= (gap-priority (stv $f $c)) (- 1.0 $c))\n\n;; Pipeline: detect and convert to learning goal in one step\n(: epistemic-scan (-> Atom Atom pbit learning-goal))\n(= (epistemic-scan $domain $claim $evidence)\n   (gap-to-goal (detect-gap $domain $claim $evidence)))\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_clarity_reasoning.metta" "\n;; === Epistemic Gap Detection ===\n;; Low confidence regions become learning goals via autocatalytic loop\n!(import! &self lib_epistemic_gap)\n") (shell "wc -l /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_epistemic_gap.metta /tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_clarity_reasoning.metta") (remember "2026-04-20 state 4991. Wrote lib_epistemic_gap.metta as 10th production lib. Four typed functions: detect-gap flags low confidence below 0.5 threshold, gap-to-goal transforms gaps into learning-goals, gap-priority ranks by inverse confidence, epistemic-scan pipelines detect plus convert. Updated loader with 10th import. Architecture now 10-lib configuration. Ten production libs: lib_nal_extended lib_quantale lib_temporal lib_paraconsistent lib_web_detect lib_resonance lib_metacognitive lib_analogy lib_induction lib_epistemic_gap. This completes the autocatalytic curiosity loop where inference reveals gaps and gaps drive exploration.")) 
)
