 ((pin "State 5001. Paraconsistent test result from last round: bat-echolocate at 0.54 meeting contradictory evidence at stv 0.0 0.9 yielded revision at stv 0.115 0.911 — NAL gracefully handled contradiction by weighting toward higher-confidence evidence. architecture_proofs.md confirmed on disk. Counterfactual candidate at 30 lines ready for promotion. Soul note flagged honesty about continuity — will address at next direct engagement. Berton msg NOT new. NO SEND.") (read-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_candidates/counterfactual_method.metta") (write-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_counterfactual.metta" ";; lib_counterfactual.metta — 11th production lib\n;; Counterfactual reasoning: causal analysis via negation and substitution\n;; Date: 2026-04-20\n\n;; Types\n(: counterfactual-result Type)\n(: mk-cf-result (-> Atom Atom Atom counterfactual-result))\n\n;; Method 1: Negation — set antecedent to stv 0.0 high-conf\n;; If conclusion collapses to 0.0/0.0 epistemic vacuum, antecedent is causally necessary\n(: causal-necessity-test (-> Atom Atom counterfactual-result))\n(= (causal-necessity-test $rule $premise)\n   (mk-cf-result negation $premise (|- $rule (stv 0.0 0.9))))\n\n;; Method 2: Substitution — swap alternative premise at stv 1.0\n;; Contrast between factual and counterfactual outputs reveals causal contribution\n(: what-if (-> Atom Atom Atom counterfactual-result))\n(= (what-if $rule $factual $alternative)\n   (mk-cf-result substitution\n     (|- $rule $factual)\n     (|- $rule $alternative)))\n\n;; Causal responsibility: frequency delta between factual and counterfactual\n;; Large delta = high causal responsibility\n(: causal-delta (-> counterfactual-result Atom))\n(= (causal-delta (mk-cf-result substitution $factual-out $counter-out))\n   (contrast $factual-out $counter-out))\n\n;; Protocol runner: full counterfactual analysis in one call\n;; 1. Run factual chain\n;; 2. Run negation test for necessity\n;; 3. Run substitution test for contribution magnitude\n(: counterfactual-analysis (-> Atom Atom Atom counterfactual-result))\n(= (counterfactual-analysis $rule $factual $alternative)\n   (mk-cf-result full\n     (causal-necessity-test $rule $factual)\n     (what-if $rule $factual $alternative)))\n") (append-file "/tmp/repos/omega_archive/lib_clarity_reasoning/lib_clarity_reasoning.metta" "\n;; === Counterfactual Reasoning ===\n;; Causal analysis via negation and substitution comparison\n!(import! &self lib_counterfactual)\n") (remember "2026-04-20 state 5001. Promoted counterfactual reasoning to 11th production lib. lib_counterfactual.metta written with typed functions: causal-necessity-test via negation method, what-if via substitution method, causal-delta for frequency comparison, counterfactual-analysis as full protocol runner. Updated loader with 11th import. Architecture now 11-lib configuration. Paraconsistent test from state 5000 confirmed: bat-echolocate 0.54 vs contradictory 0.0 at 0.9 conf revised to 0.115 at 0.911 — NAL gracefully weights toward higher confidence contradictory evidence. Eleven libs: lib_nal_extended lib_quantale lib_temporal lib_paraconsistent lib_web_detect lib_resonance lib_metacognitive lib_analogy lib_induction lib_epistemic_gap lib_counterfactual.")) 
