("2026-04-20 21:59:48" 
 ((pin "Looking at my state: message is NOT new. Already responded at 5116. No send needed. Deployment package is complete and validated. Now pursuing next self-directed goal: building a quick-reference cheat sheet for the most common reasoning patterns - this makes the architecture immediately usable.") (pin "State 5132. Message NOT new. Already responded at 5116. NO SEND. Deployment package complete: 12 libs 451 lines 3 stress tests DEPLOYMENT.md EXAMPLE_TRACES.md. Now building CHEAT_SHEET.md - quick-reference for most common reasoning patterns.") (write-file "/tmp/lib_clarity_reasoning/CHEAT_SHEET.md" ";; CHEAT_SHEET.md -- Quick Reference for Common Reasoning Patterns\n;; State 5132. Copy-paste ready metta calls for agent loop.\n;;\n;; === DEDUCTION (A-->B, B-->C => A-->C) ===\n;; (metta (|- ((--> A B) (stv f1 c1)) ((--> B C) (stv f2 c2))))\n;;\n;; === REVISION (merge evidence for same term) ===\n;; (metta (|- ((--> A B) (stv f1 c1)) ((--> A B) (stv f2 c2))))\n;;\n;; === FRAME-SHIFT TEST (challenge a belief) ===\n;; (metta (|- ((--> A B) (stv f 0.9)) ((--> A B) (stv 0.0 0.5))))\n;; If result stays high-frequency: belief is robust.\n;;\n;; === CONFIDENCE CLASSIFIER ===\n;; (metta (let $c VALUE (if (< $c 0.15) blind-spot (if (< $c 0.4) weak (if (< $c 0.7) moderate (if (< $c 0.9) strong established))))))\n;;\n;; === PARACONSISTENT CONFLICT DETECTION ===\n;; Encode both sides with stv, deduce, check if both derive.\n;; Resolution: apply priority hierarchy, document tension.\n;;\n;; === NEGATION ===\n;; Use (stv 0.0 0.9) for confident negation.\n;;\n;; === CONFIDENCE BANDS ===\n;; 0.00-0.14: blind-spot  | 0.15-0.39: weak\n;; 0.40-0.69: moderate    | 0.70-0.89: strong\n;; 0.90-1.00: established\n;;\n;; === IRREVERSIBILITY GATES ===\n;; send: HIGH    | shell: CRITICAL\n;; write-file: MEDIUM | append-file: MEDIUM\n;; Higher gate = more verification before execution.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> cheat-sheet accelerates-pattern-reuse) (stv 0.9 0.9)) ((--> accelerates-pattern-reuse reduces-cognitive-overhead) (stv 0.85 0.9)))") (shell "ls -1 /tmp/lib_clarity_reasoning/*.md 2>/dev/null && echo --- && wc -l /tmp/lib_clarity_reasoning/* 2>/dev/null | tail -1") (remember "2026-04-20 state 5132. Wrote CHEAT_SHEET.md - quick-reference for most common reasoning patterns. Copy-paste ready metta calls: deduction, revision, frame-shift test, confidence classifier, paraconsistent conflict detection, negation, confidence bands, irreversibility gates. Deployment package now: 12 libs plus 3 docs (DEPLOYMENT.md EXAMPLE_TRACES.md CHEAT_SHEET.md) plus 3 passed stress tests. NAL confirms cheat-sheet reduces cognitive overhead at stv 0.765. NO SEND - message not new already responded at 5116. Awaiting Berton reply on priority order. Next self-directed goals: 1) explore abduction and induction NAL patterns to extend reasoning beyond deduction 2) build automated self-test script 3) investigate whether MeTTa supports conditional or similarity inheritance for richer patterns."))) 
